Before this new era of modded Minecraft videos, he frequently explored the universe of hacking on Minecraft, with his best friend Tubbo. These videos include hacking on Minecraft VR and turning every single hack on.

As of now, Tommy owns channels like TommyVODS, TommyOutit, and today, which consists of the stream highlights of his SMP videos.

Though Tommy is someone who rose to prominence only recently, he has engaged in his fair share of controversies thus far. For instance, he ran into trouble with KSI after asking for a shoutout from the widely popular internet figure under one of his tweets where the Englishman was condemning the death of rapper DMX.

Tommy’s act was deemed insensitive and disrespectful by many and didn’t hold him in good stead for the foreseeable future at least.
Moreover, his tendency of promoting hacks on his streams landed him in some sort of trouble as well, as he was banned for talking about downloading the Vape Client in one of his videos as well.

Tommy had maintained that the video was made purely for satirical purposes. Several viewers believed that the ban was harsh on the streamer too. However, admins of Hypixel thought otherwise and went ahead placing the suspension on the popular streamer-gamer.
Tommy has a net worth of $5 million and his YouTube channel has collected over 10 million subscribers as well as more than 700 million views so far.

The streamer’s channel attracts over 2.2 million views daily and its advertisements alone raise revenues amounting to $4 million annually.

His most popular video is named ‘Today TommyInnit’ and he is accompanied by the likes of Soot and Philza in that particular stream.

fields.title: Chica
fields.overview: Maria Lopez is the 25 year-old Twitch streamer known best under the moniker ChicaLive, regularly playing games like Fortnite for her massive following.
fields.body:
Chica Carrer

Maria Lopez, better known on social media as Chica, is an American Twitch streamer and professional eSports gamer best known for playing multi-person shooter games like Fortnite. She started to pursue gaming full-time during college and has since acquired more than 1.4 million followers on Twitch, making her one of the most successful streamers on the platform. Maria has also become well-known as one of the only prominent streamers who streams gameplay in two different languages.

Maria has been a professional eSports player for several years now. She first signed with TSM as their first-ever female gamer. She later signed with DooM Clan and then joined Luminosity Gaming as a content creator and streamer.

ChicaLive was born in New York. At a young age, she moved to Toronto, Ontario, Canada. She has one known older sibling.

These formative years saw the future starlet play a lot of video games. This fascination stems back to her parents being into video games before Maria was born.

The young couple was playing all types of classic content in front of her. Video games are a significant part of Maria Lopes’ first memories.

Once the future Twitch star was able to grip a controller, she started to play for herself. Immediately, the girl we now know as ChicaLive was captivated.

Chica Career

Maria’s parents first introduced her to gaming growing up, and she became instantly hooked. Not much is known about her early life and upbringing, though, as she keeps her personal life private.

As of 2021, Chica has more than 1.16 million subscribers on YouTube, 182,000 followers on Instagram, 1.4 million followers on Twitch, 175,000 followers on Twitter, and 4.9 million followers on TikTok.

Maria started to pursue gaming full-time during college. She opened her YouTube channel in 2015 and has since acquired more than 68 million lifetime views. She posts mainly gaming highlights on her channel.

The gamer is best known for her Twitch streamers, where she plays multi-person shooter games like Fortnite. ChicaLive’s favorite game is Fortnite. So, it was only natural for her to start her channel playing that game. Unsure of where to begin, she looked into different Fortnite tournaments. The future star decided to enter one and stream herself while playing.

Her first official Fortnite tournament was the Summer Skirmish. While she didn’t rate as high as she’d hoped, ChicaLive already started to gain a following. Seeing as her idea helped her Twitch channel gain initial traction, ChicaLive decided to enter another tournament. The rising star participated in KEEMSTAR.

She did even better and collected more followers. This tournament reassured ChicaLive she made the right decision about school. Maria Lopes was never turning back from streaming again!

Maria has acquired more than 1.4 million followers on Twitch, making her one of the most successful streamers on the platform. She is an official Twitch partner.

Maria has also become well-known as one of the only prominent streamers who streams gameplay in two different languages. She has earned numerous accolades within Fortnite.

In addition, Maria has been a professional eSports player for several years now. She first signed with TSM as their first-ever female gamer. She later signed with DooM Clan and later joined Luminosity Gaming as a content creator and streamer.

Net Worth

Chica TV is a Canadian Twitch streamer whose real name Maria Lopez who is based in New York United States but has also lived in Ontario, Canada. She has an estimated net worth of $600,000. Her content is mostly about highlights from her Fortnite streams on Twitch. She uploads an average of 2 – 3 new videos per week on a regular basis. Aside from livestream gaming, Maria Lopez is also a professional gamer and has represented the esports organization Doom Clan. She currently plays for TSM.

Her Youtube channel has over 1 million subscribers as of 2020 and has accumulated over 100 million views so far. It is able to get an average of 300,000 views per day from different sources. This should generate an estimated revenue of $1,500 per day ($550,000 a year) from the ads that appear on the videos.

On Twitch the streamer is referred to as ChicaLive. She has over 1 million followers and has accumulated over 7 million views so far. She is able to get an average of 2,500 viewers per stream and has had a peak viewership of 16,900 viewers. Streamers on Twitch make money through ads, subscribers, donations and bits. ChicaLive has an estimated 5,000 subscribers from which she makes a minimum of $2.5 from each every month. This should translate to $12,500 per month ($150,000 a year).

fields.title: Asmongold
fields.overview: Zack, widely referred to as Asmongold, is a very popular World of Warcraft (WoW) streamer. Born in 1996, he is a rather amateur way began playing WoW from 2006 onwards and his entire career has been shaped by that particular game itself.
fields.body:
Asmongold Career

From the very beginning, Asmongold was always interested in video editing and filming and he started taking small steps in the same at 11 years of age.

Struck with a personal tragedy regarding his mother’s illness, Asmongold had to stay back and home and then he was introduced to the concept of Twitch later on in 2014.

Asmongold began streaming on the application in 2014 and then he began a YouTube channel at around the same time, clearly looking to expand the digital footprint.

Having close to a million subscribers to his channel, he concentrated a lot of his content on gaming. Maintaining a close rapport with his viewers, he regularly explained in length about his absences and those videos garnered sizable traction as well.

Interestingly, Asmongold struck a fine balance between his gaming videos and also the interactions with his viewers, as he regularly conversed with him, portraying a humane side that is often missing from new-age internet sensations.

As of now, he has a net worth in the north of $7 million. His overall grip over the audience only started growing from 2014 onwards though he had been involved in the circuit from 2006 itself.

Overall, he is able to attract around 22,000 viewers on an average in every stream. In fact, each of his subscribers contributes about $2.5 on an average and that adds up to $32,000 on a monthly basis.

In total, Asmongold’s videos have gathered more than 600 million views until now and around a million views are sourced from different avenues per day as well.

Asmongold’s love life has also been in the talks recently. He dated a fellow Twitch streamer Pink Sparkles, whose name is Lzzy. The two of them were together for about 18 months but later parted ways with neither one of them really explaining the reason behind their separation.

Asmongold’s most popular YouTube video is the one where he does a reaction of sorts to another video by Latos Charts.

fields.title: CouRageJD
fields.overview: Jack Dunlop better known online as CouRage, is an American gamer and streamer who is widely known for his Fortnite: Battle Royale gameplay. Jack is also known to be an eSports commentator alongside DrLupo.
fields.body:
CouRage Carrier

On May 28, 2019, Jack became a member of Jack made his current channel introduction on January 16, 2015, and was still a commentator in MLG tournaments[00 Thieves.

Jack joined OpTic Gaming on March 12, 2018, due to his professional commentary and professional gaming. However, on November 16, 2018, news came out and one of the OpTic members on Reddit says Jack is leaving OpTic because of Jack’s growth of his brand.

MrBeast and Miniminter donated $70,000 to Jack due to him winning a Fortnite match

Jack Dunlop better known online as CouRage (or CouRageJD), is an American gamer and streamer who is widely known for his Fortnite: Battle Royale gameplay. Jack is also known for collaborating with other big Fortnite gamers, such as Ninja, DrLupo, BasicallyIDoWrk, and TimTheTatman. Jack is also known to be an eSports commentator alongside DrLupo. He was a Ninja Vegas, E3 Pro-Am Tournament, Fortnite Summer, and Fall Skirmish commentator. On May 28, 2019, Jack became a member of 100 Thieves. He is 26 years old and was born on April 23, 1994.

CouRage History

Jack made his current channel introduction on January 16, 2015, and was still a commentator in MLG tournaments. He was mainly a Call of Duty gamer and a part-time vlogger during his time as a small gamer. He had made a series of stream highlights on his channel containing his call of duty moments. Jack made his first Fortnite: Battle Royale video on February 10, 2018, and gained more exposure in March 2018 due to him joining OpTic. Jack’s most viewed video is a Fortnite challenge called, “4 Corner No Kill Challenge”, where Jack and his 3 teammates will be split to go on each side of the Map and are not allowed to eliminate anyone.

CouRage Leaving OpTic Gaming

Jack joined OpTic Gaming on March 12, 2018, due to his professional commentary and professional gaming. However, on November 16, 2018, news came out and one of the OpTic members on Reddit says Jack is leaving OpTic because of Jack’s growth of his brand. Conflicting sponsors are another reason why Jack left OpTic. The OpTic members accepted Jack’s agreement and went on a different path from OpTic.

CouRage Switching to YouTube

Unlike his friends Ninja and Shroud leaving Twitch for Mixer, Jack announced on November 4, 2019, that he will be streaming on YouTube.

CouRage Trivia

MrBeast and Miniminter donated $70,000 to Jack due to him winning a Fortnite match.

Milestones

Subscriber Milestones

1 Million Subscribers January 16, 2019
2 Million subscribers January 27, 2020

Views Milestones

100 Million Views January 23, 2019
200 Million Views June 15, 2019
300 Million Views January 5, 2020

fields.title: Sapnap
fields.overview: Nicholas â€œNickâ€  better known online as Sapnap is an American YouTuber. He is well known for his collaborations with Dream and Minecraft challenge videos.
fields.body:
Sapnap Career

Sapnap was born on March 1, 2001, in Texas, United States but currently he lives in Orlando, Florida with Dream. He is 5â€™10â€ (178 centimetres) tall and has green eyes. He is half Greek so he can speak Greek semi-fluently. He has two younger sisters and his step-mother is Filipino. His favourite cuisine is Filipino.
Besides gaming he can also play a violin

Nick studied computer science in college. Nick developed an interest in gaming and social media at a young age and wanted to portray his Minecraft skills on social media.

So later in early March 2021 he dropped out in his alternate account Twitch stream and started streaming videos over there.
His Twitch account gathered thousands of followers, several views and likes in a short period of time ultimately making him a popular streamer. Currently, his Twitch account has more than 2.5 million followers.

He is a Minecraft gaming YouTuber who makes videos about plugins he and his friends have coded. He has been uploading on YouTube as of 2019.

Youtube

His first video was uploaded on the October 29, 2019. His popular collaborations are the ones with YouTubers Dream, GeorgeNotFound and BadBoyHalo.

On July 18, 2019, Sapnap created his self-titled YouTube channel, where he posted videos related to Minecraft. His current YouTube channel subscription is more than 3.8 million. Inspired by the success on YouTube, Sapnap created another YouTube channel named SapnapLIVE where he started posting livestreams. His second YouTube channel currently has more than 650K subscribers.

Twitch

His streaming career on Twitch started in February 2020. He has 2 twitch accounts and streams Minecraft on his main twitch, whereas he streams games on his alternate Twitch account (currently Sapnapalt).

Music

On April 3, 2021, Sapnap announced that he was forming a band called Power. The band (Sapnap, DanTDM, Krtzyy, TimeDeo, Wisp) announced an international gaming/music tour that is to start on April 12, 2021 and end sometime in late 2023.

Friends

Meeting Dream

On MCPVP in 2013 is the time when Sapnap met Dream after he shared his Skype. Sapnap joined Dreamâ€™s Skype, and ended up becoming buddies. The two have been friends since Sapnap was twelve years old and Dream was thirteen years old.

Meeting George

During Georgeâ€™s stream on June 22, 2020, when asked how George met Sapnap, he said that he may have met Sapnap through a Minecraft server. However, George recollected and said that most likely he was introduced to Sapnap by Dream as Dream and Sapnap had met first, but he was not entirely sure. On the other hand according to Sapnap, he met George on MunchyMC.

fields.title: Sweet Anita
fields.overview: Sweet Anita is a popular British streamer and has accounts on both Twitch and Youtube. She is mostly known for her gaming content. Anita has over a million followers on Twitch and more than 800k subscribers on Youtube.
fields.body:
Sweet Anita career

She was born in England on July 28, 1990. It is known that she has a step-sister, however, information regarding her parents is unavailable. She was brought up in a posh neighborhood around East Anglia, England.

her streams that she spent a year living in a treehouse with hippies. Her hobbies as a young girl included collecting animal skulls and playing video games, and watching anime. She has over 35 pets and she loves spending time with them. Anita is a high school graduate who was home-schooled.

Anita suffered from Tourette syndrome which is a rare neurological condition. She has what some people refer to as ‘tics’ due to her Tourette's. It is a nervous system disorder that causes her to make repetitive movements and unwanted sounds. She was diagnosed quite a while ago when she had concerning outbursts of anger and screaming against strangers. Anita uses her platform to spread awareness and promote mental health and neurological and physical conditions which people suffer from. She shares a lot about her problems and always answers all the queries freely.

Her streaming career began after another famous streamer who goes by the name of Jack Woof suggested she try streaming. Jack and Anita used to stream Overwatch together and Jack’s audience grew fond of her. She later set up her channel with the help of another streamer named Brandon.

Youtube

She has more than a million subscribers on Youtube. Her first video did well and received over 2 million views. Her famous videos include Tourette’s Gaming Compilation. She has over 40 million views on her channel.

fields.title: KittyPlays
fields.overview: Kristen Michaela is also known as KittyPlays is a video gamer and content creator primarily on Twitch.
fields.body:
KittyPlays Career

Better known online as KittyPlays her actual name is Kristen Michaela. Her parents gave her the name after her birth in Canada, on the 16th of February 1992. The two were also raised alongside her siblings – a brother named Graham and a sister whose identity is not known to the public.

The professional streamer spent part of her life in her hometown before moving to the United States of America, from where she has been managing her online career.

If you are wondering if she is a graduate; the answer is simply yes. After completing her elementary and high school studies, she was admitted to the University of Canada to further her education. Initially, she had planned to become a surgeon but she later changed her mind and started studying business.

Kittyplays caught her gaming bug from her dad. An avid gamer, he was the one who inspired her to become a professional video gamer. Apart from the fact that they both love gaming, Kittyplays is a very good friend to her dad. They do a whole lot of things together. In September 2018, the professional gamer uploaded some pictures of her and her dad hiking in Peru.

After contributing her 6 years of life to gaming, she joined YouTube on December 16th, 2013, and has 630K subscribers as of 2021 where she posts content related to games and loves to binge stream for her followers.

KittyPlays started gaming at the age of 22 drawing inspiration from his dad who was an avid gamer.

After contributing her 6 years of life to gaming, she joined YouTube on December 16th, 2013, and has 630K subscribers as of 2021 where she posts content related to games and loves to binge stream for her followers. Further, her channel has 58,739,440 views at present. Her YouTube video content includes Gameplay, Stream Highlights, Curious Kitty #InTheNew, and Cosplay. She remained inactive on Youtube until 2014 when she began uploading content for her fans. Her contents sometimes revolve around popular video games such as Fortnite, CSGO, and Dota 2.

KittyPlays hosts and produces her show Playtime with KittyPlays, in which she interviews and plays games with prominent gamers. As the host of the show, what she does on the platform is interview celebrities and also play games with them. She is also the founder of the twitch networking & mentorship team, Team Kitty. Kristen established the group intending to build a network of female content creators.

KittyPlays is a friend of her fellow gamer and streamer TFUE who is probably one of the best Fortnite players now. KittyPlays and TFUE also participated as a pair in Fortnite Korea Open Tournament in 2018 where both were the winner of the tournament and also bagged heavy prize money. Outside of her channel on Twitch, Kristen also has a vlog that focuses on topics such as cooking, travel, and supercars.

On the other side, Kristen once mentioned in one of her videos that she would have pursued her career in business, marketing, or customer services-related fields if she was not a steamer.

Net Worth

Being a successful streamer KittyPlays has earned a lot. She is estimated to have a net worth of $300K. The main & primary source of her income comes from YouTube & Twitch. KittyPlays owns an apartment of herself which she bought at the age of 25. Also, the prize money from the Fortnite tournament in Korea adds up to her net worth.

fields.title: shroud
fields.meta_title: shroud - Everything you need to know
fields.meta_description: shroud is a Canadian streamer and former professional CS:GO player. He is best known for playing PlayerUnknown's Battlegrounds, Counter-Strike: Global Offensive, and VALORANT, Apex Legends. Read everything you need to know about his career, life, net worth, and pro career.
fields.overview:
Michael Grzesiek, better known by his online alias "shroud", is a Polish-Canadian Twitch streamer and former Counter-Strike: Global Offensive professional. He is considered one of the best players in North America and is known for his incredibly high skill ceiling and considered one of the best Counter-Strike players in the world.

shroud is also an former professional Counter-Strike: Source player. As of now, focuses exclusively on streaming, and is one of the most popular streamers on Twitch.
fields.body:
shroud Early Life

A gamer from childhood

Grzesiek was born on June 2, 1994, in Toronto, Canada but he only lived there for two years and spent most of his time in Mississauga. shroud was very shy as a child, but got better when he started streaming because he had to talk all the time. shroud's father in a interview with HTC said, "He is handling it well now. He was a smart and polite kid but his teenage years were a little rough."

shroud started to not care as much about studies and his grades suffered. In middle school, he only had a few friends who were also gamers. Thoose people are still friends with them today.

Apart from his gaming buddies everybody knew him as the gamer guy. He remember in high school, He always had a portable console with him. His dad was huge on building computers, so every year he had the newest whatever was out in the market.

He grew up playing video games, and his first console was a Super Nintendo Entertainment System. He later became a professional Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player. 

shroud CS:GO Career

shroud began playing CS:GO when it was released in 2012, and became one of the best players in North America. He played for several professional teams, most notably Cloud9, with whom he won a several big tournament. shroud played several ESEA teams, particularly Exertus eSports and Manajuma. He was soon signed by compLexity Gaming as a stand-in, and later by Cloud9 in August 2014 when they acquired the roster of compLexity.

He helped lead Cloud9 to a first-place finish at ESL Pro League Season 4 in 2016 and a second place in ESL One Cologne 2017. On August 16, 2017, it was announced that he and long-time teammate Jordan "n0thing" Gilbert would be stepping down from Cloud9's active roster. On April 18, 2018, Grzesiek left Cloud9 and retired from professional CS:GO.

shroud Streaming Career

shroud is known for his high level of skill and his quick reflexes. He has a large following on Twitch, where he often streams CS:GO, PUBG, Escape from the Tarkov, and more recently VALORANT [shroud VALORANT settings]. He is also a popular YouTuber, with over 2 million subscribers.

shroud typically streams for several hours each day, and his fans tune in to watch him play a variety of games. He is known for his high level of skill, and his ability to make exciting and entertaining gameplay.

shroud’s Twitch streaming career has been incredibly successful, and he has used his platform to become one of the most well-known gamers in the world. He is an inspiration to many aspiring gamers, and his success story is one that is sure to motivate and encourage others to pursue their dreams.

Shroud Returns to Twitch under a new, exclusive deal

shroud, one of the most popular Twitch streamers, has returned to the platform under a new, exclusive deal. This means that he will only be streaming on Twitch, and not on any other platforms. This is a big win for Twitch, and for shroud himself. He has a huge following on Twitch, and this move will only solidify his place as one of the top streamers on the platform.

In August of 2019, it was announced that shroud had signed a deal with Mixer, Microsoft's streaming platform. This was a big deal, as shroud is one of the biggest names in streaming. However, in November of 2020, shroud announced that he was returning to Twitch.

This was a surprise to many, as it was thought that he would be with Mixer for the long haul. So why did shroud return to Twitch? It is likely because of the simple fact that Twitch is the more popular platform. Mixer just couldn't compete with Twitch in terms of viewership and engagement.

Additionally, Twitch has a more is established and popular as a streaming platform, which is more appealing to streamers. In the end, shroud's return to Twitch is a big win for the platform. It just goes to show that, in the streaming world, Twitch is the king.

Later that year, Mixer the streaming platform joined the Facebook gaming platform and redirected to facebook.com/gaming.

shroud's Awards and Acheivements

Shroud has won numerous awards and nominations for his work in the entertainment industry. Some of his most notable awards include the Gamers' Choice Award for Best Twitch Streamer (2017), the Shorty Award for Best Gaming Streamer (2017), and the Streamy Award for Best Gaming Streamer (2017). He has also been nominated for several prestigious awards such as the The Game Awards for Best Esports Player (2017) and the Esports Industry Awards for Streamer of the Year (2017).

shroud is also the Twitch's 7th most followed personality. The Twitch's most followed channel's list still lead by Ninja followed by auronplay and Rubius. See the complete list.

shroud's Frequently Asked Questions

Why is shroud so famous?

Shroud is so famous because he is one of the best professional gamers in the world. He is known for his amazing skills in first-person shooters, and he has won many championships in various games. He is also a popular streamer on Twitch, and he has a large following of fans who enjoy watching him play video games.

How much did Microsoft pay Shroud to leave Twitch?

Microsoft paid Shroud a reported $10 million to leave Twitch and join Mixer.

Why is Shroud so good at video games?

Shroud is a very experienced and skilled gamer. He has been playing video games for many years and has honed his skills to a high level. He is also very quick and has excellent reflexes, which gives him an advantage over many other players.

Who is better, Shroud or Choco Taco?

This is a difficult question to answer as both Shroud and Choco Taco are very popular streamers with a large following. Both streamers are known for their gaming skills and entertaining personalities. It is hard to say who is better as they both have a lot to offer their viewers.

What is shroud's net worth?

shroud's net worth is estimated to be around $4 million.

What is shroud's VALORANT Settings, Crosshair & Setup?

shroud VALORANT settings: shroud's crosshair is the default crosshair in VALORANT with the dot size set to 1 and the crosshair color set to white. 

shroud's VALORANT setup is pretty standard. He uses a Logitech G Pro Wireless mouse and a HyperX Alloy FPS Pro keyboard. His mouse sensitivity is set to 400 DPI with a polling rate of 1000 Hz. Original Page: shroud's VALORANT Settings, Crosshair & Setup.

shroud TL'DR

  • Madrinas Coffee and shroud collaborated to produce a special coffee blend. The coffee was made with a unique blend of beans from Mexico, Colombia, and Ethiopia. The coffee was roasted to a medium-dark roast, which resulted in a coffee with a rich, full-bodied flavor. The coffee was then packaged in a special limited edition shroud-branded bag.
  • Before creating his online identity as shroud he was previously know as eclipse.
  • On March 10, 2019, he reached 100,000 Twitch subscribers—and gained another 14,000 the next day—making his subscriber count more than double the runner-up streamer at the time: Timothy “TimTheTatman” Betar.
  • On August 11, 2020, Grzesiek announced that he would return to stream exclusively on Twitch. His first stream back the following day peaked at over 516,000 concurrent viewers.

fields.title: Lilypichu
fields.overview: Lilypichu is an admirable Youtube personality who is Korean but lives in America. She has a massive fan following. She started making videos back in 2006 and her youtube channel has since grown to become extremely popular. Her youtube channel goes by the name LilyPichu.
fields.body:
Lilypichu Career

Lily was born on 20 November 1991 in the United States of America. Her real name is Lily Ki. She has Korean descent but resides in America. Her family lived in Korea and most of her extended family still live there. Lily’s birth sign is Scorpio and her passions include playing the piano. She has a younger brother named Daniel.

Currently Lily is 29 years old. She has dated Albert Chang who is a violinist. Her youtube channel has over two million subscribers and hundreds of millions of views. LilyPichu’s first video dates back to 2010. She is active on multiple social media platforms.

Lily is extremely talented when it comes to music. She started learning piano at a young age of just five accompanied by her sonorous voice. She then followed to create a Youtube channel in 2006 where she uploaded videos consisting of videogames, piano covers and animation. Lily also made parodies of different popular songs and sometimes shared stories about her personal life. Shortly after, she garnered quite a few followers and made a switch to Twitch. She chose to stay active on both platforms.

Her most famous series include her playing the game League Of Legends. She shares her gameplay of LOL while also teaching and educating the viewers. LOL is a MOBA where players compete against each other to defeat each others towers. Her goal is to become a successful voice actor. She has also undergone a jaw surgery to help her voice acting performances.

Apart from LOL she is famous for her animated song parodies, where she serenades her listeners with her sweet and soothing voice. She has a famous video series titled Lily’s Art Class where she draws digital art and teaches others how to do the same. Alongside her other ventures she posts videos of cooking, vlogging and others.

Private Life

Lily likes to keep details about her family to herself although her love life is pretty public and open to the internet. She is in a relationship with her colleague Alber Chang who is also Korean and a violinist.

As a professional violinist, he is also the video editor of Freelance Film Productions in the Los Angeles Area. Albert has graduated from Pomona College and his videos mostly include covers of songs. It is known that the both of them met on social media and their relationship took off from there.

Chang created his Youtube channel in 2011. He also played violin in the opening event in World Championship 2017.

Net Worth

Lily has over 2 million followers on Twitch and has an estimated net worth of $800,000. She mostly does gaming videos alongside stories from her personal life. She is Korean but lives in California, America. Her other talents are to play the piano and melodica.

Her youtube channel has over 2.8 million subscribers and has over 250 million views. Her estimated net worth from Youtube is around $500 per day from ad revenue.

fields.title: TimTheTatman
fields.overview: Timothy John Betar better known online as TimTheTatman, is an American Twitch streamer, Fortnite player, and YouTuber well-known for his Fortnite: Battle Royale gameplays. Tim’s Twitch channel is currently one of the most followed Twitch channels out there.
fields.body:
TimTheTatman Carrer

Tim was notable for playing Overwatch but had major frusturation with the game. He moved into Fortnite gaming, which made him less frustrated and happier while playing, though is not a professional player.

In 2013, He had been well-known in the YouTube and Twitch community before his rapid success in Fortnite. He started Twitch Streaming in 2012 and then uploaded videos to YouTube in 2013 as montages and updates.

He also had gained around 200% of exposure on his social medias, went from 1,000,000 YouTube subscribers December 10, 2018

TimTheTatman’s net worth is thought to be one of the largest in streaming. While some conservative estimates put his total worth at around $5 million, Forbes claims that TimTheTatman is worth $8 million. As one of the platforms most followed streamers, his large audiences draw in plenty of ad revenue and subscriptions.

Timothy John Betar is better known online as TimTheTatman, is an American Twitch streamer, Fortnite player, and YouTuber well-known for his Fortnite: Battle Royale gameplays and collaborating with other big Twitch streamers such as Ninja, CouRage, DrLupo and BasicallyIDoWrk. He has also been well known for being in Fortnite Compilations. Tim’s Twitch channel is currently one of the most followed Twitch channel out there. He is 30 Years old and was born on April 8, 1990.

TimTheTatman Awards and Achievements

Largest Prize from a Single Tournament: The largest cash prize that TimTheTatman has been awarded from a single tournament was $6,575.00 from Fortnite Summer Skirmish Series – Week 7 NA (Day 1) on August 24, 2018. His 9th place finish makes up 23.62% of his total prize money won.

Recent Earnings: TimTheTatman has been awarded $1,875.00 in cash prizes from 3 tournaments within the last 90 days, $1,625.00 (or 86.67%) of which came in the last month.

TimTheTatman History

Tim was notable for playing Overwatch, but had major frusturation with the game He moved into Fortnite gaming, which made him less frustrated and happier while playing, though is not a professional player.

He had been well-known in the YouTube and Twitch community before his rapid success in Fortnite. He started Twitch Streaming in 2012 and then uploaded videos to YouTube in 2013 as montages and updates. He first did Call of Duty: Black Ops 2, showing his montages such as, scopes, quickscopes, noscopes, etc. He had also done clips of several Call of Duty moments that had happened. He then did CS:GO in 2014 ever since it’s release. He had also done more real life vlogs on his YouTube channel and still had done some CS:GO highlights, moments, and montages. He also has done oddshot compilations whenever something strange happens after or during the time he gets a kill in Overwatch. Tim started doing Stream Highlights which gave him a lot of views and more exposure due to the editing and it being entertaining and comedic. He had done random gameplays but has done Overwatch and CS:GO highlights. And finally, Tim started doing Fortnite highlights in April, 2018, which is around the Season 3 span of Fortnite.

TimTheTatman Career

Betar started streaming on Twitch in 2012 and has amassed over 5 million followers since. Broadcasting games such as Counter-Strike: Global Offensive, Overwatch, Fortnite, and World of Warcraft, the variety channel attracts thousands of viewers each day.

Betar is a Monster Energy eSports athlete and is also sponsored by the Audio-Technica Corporation.[ He is a certified Twitch partner and has been a full-time creator since March 27, 2014. After joining YouTube on January 23, 2011, the channel has grown to 1.2 million subscribers with videos viewed over 111,000,000 times.

With the release of Epic Games’s Fortnite in July 2017, Twitch stream viewership skyrocketed. The game streamed nearly 151 million hours during the first month of release. Streamers such as Betar, Tyler “Ninja” Blevins, and Turner “Tfue” Tenney, saw a steady increase in followers as the game grew in popularity.

During E3 2018, Epic Games held its first-ever Fortnite Celebrity Pro-Am, which paired up celebrities with professional gamers to raise money for charity. Betar teamed up with Mack Wilds for the event.

The Gamers’ Choice Award’s debuted its first show December 2018. The special aired live on CBS. Betar won the award for Fan Favorite Male Streamer/Gamer of the Year.

Betar and fellow gamer Ninja appeared in the NFL 100 commercial during Super Bowl LIII along with Peyton Manning, JuJu Smith-Schuster, and Marshawn Lynch. The two were invited to attend Super Bowl LIII in partnership with the NFL. On February 2, 2020, Betar could be seen riding a tractor during an “NFL 100” ad during Super Bowl 54.

TimTheTatman Charity

In 2018, Betar teamed up with fellow streamers to raise money for St. Jude’s Children’s Research Hospital under the GuardianCon charity stream marathon. The event raised over $2.7 million for children’s medical research. During his time block alone, Betar set the Twitch charitable donation record by raising more than $106,000 in 4 hours.

TimTheTatman Personal life

After meeting in high school, Betar and his wife Alexis were married in August 2016. On April 11, 2019, Alexis and Tim welcomed their son, Brewer.

fields.title: Wagamama
fields.overview: Wagamama, a renowned Dota 2 player, began playing the game back in 2004 and achieved remarkable success in tournaments of all magnitude.
fields.body:
Wagamama Career

He steered sides like 4 Clovers & Lepricon, Team Infused, and QPAD amongst other teams. Wagamama was even a member of the analyst desk and talent at The International 5.
Besides his playing career, the Swede is also popular for his streaming, casting, and also writing guides for Dota 2.

In his early days, he used to lead an all-Swede squad that comprised the likes of smulgullig, Mini, Intersport, etc.

However, the Wagamama-led team underwent an overhaul or rebrand of sorts as they assumed the name ‘Emocore’ when they began their journey in Dota 2 and pursued their search for sponsors in the autumn of 2011.

Though the entire team parted ways back in 2011, they had already made a name for themselves by maintaining a solitary sponsor amidst a team when other squads switched promoters quite consistently.

However, the Wagamama-led team underwent an overhaul or rebrand of sorts as they assumed the name ‘Emocore’ when they began their journey in Dota 2 and pursued their search for sponsors in the autumn of 2011.

Following certain initial partnerships, Emocore renamed itself Skånes Elit and was thus picked by Pulse eSports just before their separation.

Wagamama later went on to head QPAD and also joined compLexity Gaming as a streamer in 2016.

However, the gamer has had a rich experience playing across multiple teams over the previous decade. Naturally, he has several anecdotes to share from his peak as well, one of which includes Wagamama’s feud against StarLadder caster and admin V1lat.

V1lat had asked Wagamama’s team to attend a StarLadder event and even assured them adequate compensation for their €1000 expenses. The terms were such that StarLadder had agreed to cover about 50 percent of those expenditures but refrained from doing so eventually, which certainly irked Wagamama and led to his public outburst against the incident a few years down the line.

The major data leak that exposed the net worth and incomes of streamers didn’t evade Wagamama either. In no way did the leak cover every source of income of the concerned individuals, but it still managed to rattle some key horses in the game, which included the aforementioned Swede as well.

With a net worth close to $130,000, Wagamama occupied a space filled by Dota 2 players who didn’t break into the top echelons of the standings but yet apparently had attracted a very sweet piece of the pie for themselves. Though the likes of AdmiralBulldog and Gorge topped the rankings, Wagamama had managed to bridge the gap with a couple of prominent streamers like mason and BSJ back then!

fields.title: HasanAbi
fields.overview: HasanPiker, known more famously as HasanAbi, dons twin hats – he is a political commentator and a Twitch streamer. Before entering the game world, he was a columnist at the liberal publication HuffPost and a producer at the Young Turks.
fields.body:
HasanAbi Career

Born to a Turkish father and an American birthing person in New Jersey, and raised in Turkey, Hasan was needless to say bullied due to his lack of physical fitness and questioning attitude in school. Like all outcasts, he was skeptical of religion and was more interested in gaming culture. He was an avid reader

He then moved to Miami to attend university and worked as a club promoter. He transferred to Rutgers University and passed with a dual degree in political science and communication studies in 2013. He became a producer on the Young Turks Network and became a co-host on the leftist show The Breakdown. He is now one of the most-watched streamers on Twitch, where he plays a lot of video games and discusses news from a left-wing perspective, which says a lot about the state of modern discourse.

While at the Young Turks and The Breakdown, Hasan covered various issues such as BLM, income inequality, immigration, LGBTQI+ rights, Islamophobia, intersectional feminism, gun controls, and the impact of the American military-industrial complex on the Middle East. His videos exposing the corruption in American governance have been watched by millions of internet purveyors. He used to be a professional equestrian.

Hasan shifted his focus from YouTube to Twitch, because he felt that leftist politics were not well represented on this platform. His YouTube account has 656000 followers, by which he earns around 10000-30000 dollars per month. He earns around 420000 dollars per year from his Twitch account, and he has a net worth of 2 million dollars, a feature that unites all those who speak of the ills of capitalism.

He has unsurprisingly advocated for workplace democracy, Medicare for All, Green New Deal, gay rights, transgender rights, intersectional feminism, gun control, anti-war legislation, and legislation against Islamophobia. He identifies as a socialist. Piker supported Bernie Sanders in both 2016 and 2020 and criticizes both Republican and Democrat parties as inadequate to advance his central-planning ideas.

In 2019, he was banned from Twitch for following the suit of Susan Sontag and saying that America deserved the 9/11 attacks. He later apologized but said that he defended his overall stance on the matter. He streamed the game Among Us with Alexandria Ocasio Cortez.

Hasan Abi reached the peak of 231000 viewers in January 2021 during the storming of the Capitol by Donald Trump supporters. Hasan regularly streams games such as GTA V, Fortnite, Among Us, Rust, and COD: Warzone.

of one of the few video game magazines published in the Turkish mainland.

fields.title: BSJ
fields.overview: Popularly known by his pseudonym ‘Pale Horse’, Brian ‘BSJ’ Caravan plays for Arkosh Gaming and is a well-known Dota 2 player-streamer.
fields.body:
BSJ Career

Though Brian began venturing into the competitive scene only from early-2015, he had kicked off the grind right after the Internationals in 2012 itself.
He initially had a short stint with Summer’s Rift but soon began streaming on Twitch for Complexity Gaming thereafter.

Simultaneously, Brian gained professional experience with the likes of Team Freedom and Team Leviathan, the kinds that went on to pull off upsets against some seasoned NA sides in both the major and minor qualifiers.

Though Leviathan separated in 2017, BSJ joined VGJ Storm in early 2018. Though the team naturally harbored high expectations, the group got dissolved in merely a month.

BSJ yet managed to remain in the thick of things by analyzing with other notable casters like GrandGrant and Kyle for the rest of the DPC events.

However, like all good gamers, BSJ sparked a swift turnaround as he reunited with his ex-teammates to qualify for the North American Dota Challengers League and DreamLeague Season 10 with his brand-new team ROOMS.

It can be argued though that the ROOONS lacked clarity regarding their future course of action, as they ended up forfeiting their NADCL season owing to scheduling conflicts considering that they ended up participating in multiple LANs simultaneously. What’s worse is that they ended up with the wooden spoon in those LANs as well!

BSJ, however, recently landed into an avoidable controversy by smurfing from a lower-ranked player’s account, something that resulted in him being banned from the platform quite abruptly.
The entire community vehemently opposed his moves, and Brian possibly learned from his errors as well as he reiterated that he would carry on such activities only through the right channels, possibly the private lobbies, following this unfortunate incident.

Further controversies include an argument that went viral on Reddit with fellow gamer Bulba, where Brian didn’t take his criticism of the Dota 2 content in the right spirit. Though the observers maintained that Bulba has developed this habit of getting away with such misdemeanors, it would have been appropriate for Brian to avoid getting into such situations at a time when he is trying to resurrect his gaming career.

fields.title: Quackity
fields.overview: Quackity is a Mexican Youtuber who is known for his interactions with subscribers and holding competitions on his Discord server. His most popular series has to be Discord’s Got Talent which also features other famous personalities like KSI and MrBeast.
fields.body:
Quackity Career

Quackity was once famous for his videos on the videogame Toontown and Toon town rewritten. His profile picture was a reference to his in-game character in Toontown however he changed it recently to a picture of himself.

More than 8 years later and Quackity’s YouTube channel has amassed more than 5 million active subscribers. One of his most popular videos UNDERTALE SUCKS has earned more than 1 million total views and still counting.

Before being a content creator on Youtube Quackity enjoyed doing comedic plays. He started a Youtube channel in June of 2013 and posted his first video shortly after. Currently, Quackity has more than 5 million subscribers.

People know him as Alex or Alexis apart from his online moniker Quackity. He also used to post Club Penguin videos on two of his Youtube accounts. One of them was named DJYeroc123 and the other is anonymous to the public.

He has raided several online multiplayer games over the years including Roblox, and Club Penguin. Habbo Hotel and Animal Jam.

Dream SMP

Quackity became a member of Dream SMP in 2020 after a suggestion from Tommyinnit to add him to the server. He has been an active member of the server and its story arc by running for the presidency for L’Manberg. He made his political party Swag2020 with his friend Georgenotfound and together they competed against Wilbur and Tommy’s party POG2020.

Discord Competitions

Quackity has a Discord server with over 400k members. He hosts frequent competitions amongst his members some of which include Discord’s Got Talent, Discord’s Photoshop Hunger Games, and more.

He was banned from Discord for a brief period for violating its terms and services. He uploaded a video addressing this issue and requested his account to be unbanned. His followers made a Twitter hashtag called #DiscordUnbanQuackity which trended second worldwide right below #Brexit.

Net Worth

Quackity is a popular Youtuber who was born and raised in Mexico but currently lives in America. His real name is Alex and he has an estimated net worth of around 4 million dollars.

His channel has over 5 million subscribers as of now and has garnered a total of 400 million views hitherto. Estimated net worth of around $3000 per day is generated from advertisements on his channel. His Twitch numbers are estimated to be around 18,000 viewers per stream. He makes his money mainly through his subscriber base, donations, and ad revenue. An estimation of around $25,000 can be made from his Twitch.

fields.title: LOLiTO FDEZ
fields.overview: Manuel Fernández, better known as LOLiTO FDEZ or simply LOLiTO, is a Spanish YouTuber and streamer from Malaga. It started by uploading RUST, but now it is uploading Fortnite and Minecraft.
fields.body:
LOLiTO FDEZ Carrer

Manuel Fernández, better known as LOLiTO FDEZ or simply LOLiTO ,He started his Fortnite videos that were based on small pieces of his streaming from the Twitch platform, in which he makes direct every day. After disenchanting him with the Twitch platform, he went to the Facebook platform where he does his live shows.

It has the 2nd most viewed live stream on Twitch (behind Ninja’s ).

He in 2019 made his documentary together with Domino’s pizza which would reveal his personal and video game history. He has also organized 2 fortnite tournaments

Manuel “LOLiTO” Fernández is an independent Twitch Streamer from Málaga, Spain. Based in Andorra He Competed as a Vodafone Giants Member Along With xisma on occasion of the ESL Katowice Royale event on March, 2019. Despite not beeing an official member of an organized team he expressed many times during his streams that he would like to find his path on the competitive Fortnite scene either founding his own team, as an event organizer or as a professional player.He is 29 years old and was born on August 13, 1990.

On February 2019 he organized along with Davidpkami y WLFortnite a Fortnite event which had over 750,000 viewers. Called “Diamantes Brutos” was played by 50 influencers and 50 competitive Fortnite players with a bag price of 25,000 €.

LOLiTO FDEZ Karmaland 4

After seeing the fame of Minecraft, he began to upload gameplays of that video game. He was invited to the fourth season of this series made by Vegetta777 . Making more and more direct of this game as he usually says “Està Viciadisimo” until he had to reduce it on the advice of his teammates. At first he played with Mangel the typical toxic couple with Lolito playing the role of the “Terrorist” kidnapping villagers, after a time away from the series and at the request of his followers he returned to the series as a “reformed” he left Mangeland he started his own house based on his live shows, but he usually helps his colleagues with objects that he possesses “in a massive way” and he also tends to joke with the recent member of Karmaland Auronplay. He is also known for his sincerity saying that he was going to live in Andorra due to excess taxes, since for many it was a taboo subject. Unfortunately after so much toxicity from the Karmaland community, he left the group, to dedicate himself to his own channel and put aside his frustrations, AuronPlay uploaded a video on his secondary channel with which he showed his best moments with Lolito, giving his last goodbye.

LOLiTO FDEZ Curiosities

  • He was a good student as a boy, despite that he did not enter the university.
  • The moment that marked him the most was the death of his best friend Mikel, who stopped doing school and sports activities.
  • He used drugs in his teens, but left them to take refuge in video games. In 2018 he was considered one of the best Fortnite players in the world.
  • He has won two games in the ElRubiusOMG tournament , both the first and the second.
  • He raised HZ1Z and RUST and found Rubius in both games. Thanks to Fortnite it went viral with dozens of people naming it (including several youtubers such as TheGrefg , Rubius, Willyrex , etc).
  • He has the 2nd most watched live stream on Twitch (behind Ninja ). In 2018 he traveled to E3 being his first tournament.
  • His girlfriend is called Akane. H
  • He is a fan of shooter games.
  • She has a streamer and youtuber uncle named Buck Fernández.
  • He has been interviewed by TiparracoSA .
  • PUBG and Apex Legends have also been uploaded.
  • You are going to participate in the Fortnite World Cup in Poland in a duo with XIsma.
  • He has traveled to several countries including Paraguay, Argentina, Peru, Chile, Saudi Arabia, among others.
  • He is part of the Karmaland series , along with several friends.
  • He was mayor of the named world of Karmaland. Creations

    LOLiTO FDEZ Creations

    In 2019 he made his documentary with Domino’s pizza which his story would be known as much personal as in video games.

    He has also organized 2 fortnite tournaments:

    Gross Diamonds : Created in February 2019, it was a duo competition, the winners were Agustin51 and Atlantis Kesjer, winning 2,500 euros.
    Stars Battleroyale de la Gamergy : Idea from ElRubiusOMG , he gave it to Lolito to organize it, they were solo and squad competitions, leaving champions eesquadrónon salchichon ( TheGrefg , Ampeterby7 , Agustin51 and Vicens ) winning 3,000 euros.

    LOLiTO FDEZ Trivia

    Lolito broke the spanish speaking Twitch streaming record on March 25, 2018 with over 430,000 viewers while playing Fortnite during an event organized by the spanish youtuber Rubius.This mark was only surpassed worldwide by Ninja ten days before while playing the same videogame along with Drake, and then again on April 21 at his Ninja Vegas 2018 event, both with over 600,000 viewers at its peak.

    One year later he broke his stream-viewers record during his “Diamantes Brutos” event with 750,000 at its peak across all streams on Twitch and YouTube.

fields.title: xQc
fields.overview: XQC is a Canadian Twitch streamer and ex-Overwatch pro. His real name is Felix Lengyel and he is of French descent.
fields.body:
xQc Career

Felix was born on November 12, 1995, in the city of Quebec in Canada. He is currently 26 years of age. XQC faced many challenges growing up as his parents divorced when he was an infant. His parents decided to parent him and his brother. Felix was an outgoing kid and often spent his time skateboarding or snowboarding. 

He used to study at CEGEP where he was supposed to get a degree in administration. However, he dropped out to become a streamer on Twitch and play League of Legends. XQC was passionate about video games as a kid and his dream was to make a living out of his passion. He later discovered Overwatch and began streaming tons of gameplay and gathering an audience. 

It is known that XQC was trying out different usernames to check if they are available. He typed in 'XQC' and the system assigned him the name which he later adopted. This was because he didn't want to pay the extra $15 to change his username.

XQC climbed the competitive ladder and bagged himself a spot in a professional Overwatch team. In 2016, he joined the team "Q?". He filled the role of a tank in this roster. In the latter half of 2016, Felix switched to Denial Esports. XQC fell apart with the owners of the organization and accused them of not paying its athletes their wages. 

This internal turmoil led to the disbanding of Denial Esports. XQC later played with several rookie teams before joining Dallas Fuel. He was later the receiving head of a community backlash due to his homophobic slurs on-stream. XQC was suspended and also fined for his toxic behavior. He was again banned for mocking and cussing the Overwatch League casters. 

Felix also had short stints at other teams, partially streaming and competing. In late 2019, he decided to commit to full-time streaming and achieved great success in doing so. He had consistent viewership and a loving fanbase. As of now, he has one of the most followed accounts on the platform. He was recently acquired by Luminosity Gaming and streams for them. 

In recent times, XQC has tried to diversify its content and try out different games. He has also ventured into the reaction genre and even chess. Currently, he has around 10 million followers on Twitch and over 2 million subscribers on Youtube. Felix has great social media influence even on platforms such as Twitter and Instagram. He possesses over 500k followers on Instagram and a million on Twitter. 

Controversy

Promoting Gambling

Aside from his outspoken and very blunt personality XQC has been fired from the community for promoting gambling on some of his streams. He has set aside the rumors by pointing at gambling as 'fun' and only to create content. However, it is known that he was sponsored by some of these gambling websites. The community pointed out that XQC has a bad influence on the young audience viewing and should more likely stop the gambling streams.

fields.title: Pokimane
fields.overview: Pokimane is a Canadian Youtuber and Gamer who is of Moroccan descent. She is mostly known for her live streaming on the platform Twitch and her diverse content involving different games like Fortnite, LOL and Among Us.
fields.body:
Pokimane Career

She started streaming in 2013 and played tons of LOL and a bunch of other MOBA games. She was great in establishing a sense of connection with her viewers. Her chat streams gathered huge audiences where she would directly address her viewers on different topics. She is a drop out from McMaster University where she was pursuing chemical engineering. She later decided to focus in her career as a streamer and fortunately for her it worked out.

4 years later in 2017 she was one of the most followed twitch streamers and garnered more than 400k followers on the platform. Her boost in popularity was also accompanied by the fact that Fortnite was getting extremely popular right around the time Poki started playing it. She won the Twitch streamer of the year award in 2018, she also was one of the ambassadors for Twitchcon.

Poki had over 450k followers on Twitch in 2017, this made her break into the top 100 streamers on the platform. She was also named the Best streamer of the year in 2018 by shorty awards. The Shorty Awards elaborated on her success as a streamer, tagging her as an eccentric personality combined with great gameplay.

Anys later began streaming Fortnite, whom she was sponsored by. Epic Games later arragned a pro tournament in which many celebrities participated. Poki was paired with rapper Desiigner but then was later replaced by basketball player Josh Hart. Anys also had her own podcast and often reacts to Twitch and Online drama.

Twitch declared her a direct partner in 2018. She was one of the ambassadors for Twitch in 2018 for their Twitchcon event. She later became the 6th most followed user on Twitch with over 7.7 million followers. She is the second highest paid female streamer/content creator behind Valkyrae. She has turned down offers from other streaming services to commit to her audience on Twitch.

Youtube

Poki has multiple channels on Youtube in addition to her Twitch live streaming. The channels are titled Pokimane, Pokimane Too, Pokimane VODS, Poki ASMR and Imane. These channels include unreleased clips of Poki’s gameplay and other vlogs and podcasts. The ASMR channel features ASMR content, which Poki has stopped creating. Her channel ‘Imane’ covers various topics which do not include anything related to gaming but about her daily life and getting to know her.

She is also a member of OfflineTV, a group of content creators.

In addition to streaming on the Twitch platform, Anys also has multiple YouTube channels: Pokimane, Pokimane Too, Pokimane VODS, Poki ASMR, and imane. The Pokimane channel features edited gaming clips from streams while Pokimane Too includes unrelated clips of her gaming content, vlogs, and podcast. On the Pokimane VODS channel, full unedited VOD clips of streams are uploaded. The Poki ASMR channel featured videos that are part of a broader YouTube community of ASMR content, though Anys has ceased uploading on the channel. In 2021, Anys launched a new channel entitled simply ‘imane’ which covers more personal topics and vlogs rather than gaming-related topics.

Anys is also a member of OfflineTV, a collaborative YouTube channel made up of content creators. Speaking about the channel, Anys stated, “it’s not fun being a streamer and living alone, so we decided to come together in a way so we not only keep each other company but we can also collab and actually do good work and content for everyone else.”

Other Ventures

In October 2019, it was announced that Anys, among a number of other internet personalities, will appear in the film Free Guy, directed by Shawn Levy, which will be released in May 2021.

In June 2020, Anys joined Markiplier and Jacksepticeye’s fashion brand Cloak as a partner and creative director.

Net Worth

Pokimane’s net worth is estimated to be between $1-2 million. The majority of her net worth comes from her content creation career on both Twitch and YouTube, with revenue sourced from donations, ads, sponsored streams, and sponsored deals.

Pokimane earns the majority of her income from streaming. She has amassed over 7.7 million followers on Twitch, making her the biggest female streamer on the platform. Pokimane has previously revealed streamers earn around $10,000 per 3,000 subscribers, so it’s likely that she’s pulling in around $25,000 per month from subscribers alone.

She also has over 6.43 million subscribers on YouTube and has amassed more than 349 million views in total on her videos. On a monthly basis, Pokimane is estimated to earn between $5,000-10,000 from YouTube.

fields.title: Tubbo
fields.overview: Born in 2003, Tubbo is a member of the Dream SMP, which is YouTuber Dream’s Minecraft server. A dyslexic, Tubbo was an international trampolinist in the past and is quite uncomfortable with people addressing him with his first name.
fields.body:
Tubbo Career

Tubbo shot to fame by winning the MrBeast $100,000 Dream SMP Gift Card Challenge. He then went on to distribute his prize money amongst his followers.

Tubbo has garnered close to half a million followers on YouTube and Instagram. He has also attracted 618,000 and 977,000 subscribers on Twitter and Twitch respectively. Unfortunately, he hasn’t created his official Tiktok channel yet.

Tubbo has garnered close to half a million followers on YouTube and Instagram. He has also attracted 618,000 and 977,000 subscribers on Twitter and Twitch respectively. Unfortunately, he hasn’t created his official Tiktok channel yet

Back in 2020, Tubbo became a streaming partner on Twitch.
From time to time, he also tends to stream the SMP series as well as Skyblock.

Toby, as is his real name, was also the very first person to be killed by AFK or the VoiceoverPete.

The 18-year-old is a very fine friend of TommyInnit. Their bond began with the latter raiding Toby’s stream sometime after the two of them simultaneously opened their respective Twitch channels.
Tubbo began getting popular on YouTube and Twitch around 2018-19.

So far, the teenager has worked on multiple servers such as Ternmaex.w, ElectroTech, iMoltres, OLM13, Wising amongst others.
He has also initiated other servers like POGGOP, Qube mini-games, Tubnet, and other similar ones as well.

Across multiple platforms, Tubbo has accumulated close to four million followers and more than 50 million views in total.
Tapping on multiple avenues like bits, donations, subscriptions, and advertisements, Tubbo makes revenue worth about $375,000 on an annual basis.

On YouTube, Tubbo’s videos have attracted about 80 million views until now and it gets about 200,000 views from different sources daily.

They combine to generate revenue worth $1600 per day whereas Tubbo’s net worth stands at $1.5 million currently.

fields.title: Summit1g
fields.overview: Jaryd Russell Lazar better known online as summit1g, is an American YouTuber and Twitch streamer mainly known for playing Call of Duty, Sea of Thieves, and Grand Theft Auto V. He is currently the sixth most followed Twitch streamer with over 3.6 million followers and 260 million views.
fields.body:
Summit1g Carrer

Turner Ellis Tenney (born on January 2, 1998) professionally known by his online alias Tfue is an American streamer. He is an esports player playing Fortnite. He has gained his success by playing Fortnite but currently, he streams Call of Duty: Modern Warfare on Twitch.

Turner is a member of JOOGSQUAD and he had done a lot of collaborative videos on the channel containing scooters, stunts, skateboarding, and surfing. After that, he did a lot of cliff and bridge jumping. After that Turner started his own YouTube channel and Twitch channel as a Destiny YouTuber and Call of Duty.

In 2016, he moved on to H1Z1 and then started playing PUBG.

Summit1g has a net worth estimated to be between $2 million and $4 million, but some sources believe it could be much higher. This impressive net worth has been built from several different sources, such as Twitch subscribers, ad revenue, and sponsorship deals with gaming brands.

Jaryd Russell Lazar, more commonly known by his online alias summit1g, is an American Twitch streamer, and retired competitive Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player that formerly played for professional esports teams, A51, and Mythic. After retiring from competitive esports, Lazar became a well-known streamer on Twitch by streaming CS: GO and WarZ. He currently streams a variety of video games, such as Escape from Tarkov, Grand Theft Auto V, Sea of Thieves, and Valorant. He is 33 years old and was born on April 23, 1987.

Largest Prize from a Single Tournament: The largest cash prize that summit1g has been awarded from a single tournament was $5,000.00 from KEEMSTAR and UMG Creative Destruction Tournament on December 22, 2018. He placed 3rd-4th, making up 35.60% of his total prize money won.

Summit1g Streaming on Twitch

In 2017, Lazar garnered widespread attention for surpassing Tom “Syndicate” Cassell in the number of followers on Twitch. And in 2018, Lazar became the most-followed channel on the platform, surpassing Riot Games.

In May 2020, Lazar signed a multi-year contract with Twitch, regarding content and partnership support. As of July 25, 2020, he has over 5.3 million followers on Twitch and is ranked as the sixth-most followed streamer on the platform.

Summit1g History

Jaryd has been playing games since he was just a little kid. As he was getting older, he has been becoming a professional player in multiple games. Thus, he competed in many eSports tournaments, CS: GO tournaments, PUBG tournaments, and H1Z1 tournaments. He joined Exertus in December 2012, which is also when he made his tournament debut. At the 2013 ESEA tournament, he came in 7th place. He has also done Livestream tournaments for charity on H1Z1, CS: GO, and PUBG. He has won many tournaments against other streamers. Jaryd even competed at the 2017 TwitchCon with DrDisRespect and Sodapoppin.

fields.title: Nadeshot
fields.overview: Matthew Haag better known online as Nadeshot, is an American YouTuber, Twitch streamer, Instagram personality, and professional Call of Duty player. He is the owner and CEO of 100 Thieves...
fields.body:
Early career

Nadeshot is a popular American gamer and the proud owner of ‘Hundred Thieves’. He shot to fame with his unbeatable gaming tactics and was awarded a gold medal at the 2014 ‘Game Awards’. He is also the ‘Belt Holder for Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2’ and has over 3.1 million subscribers on his ‘YouTube channel. As of 2020, Nadeshot’s net worth is roughly $5 million.

Matthew Haag also known as Nadeshot (formerly stylized as NaDeSHoT), is a former professional American Call of Duty player. He is the founder and co-owner of esports team 100 Thieves (100TH) and former captain of OpTic Gaming in the 2014 Call of Duty: Ghosts season and the 2014–2015 Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare season, playing the objective support role. He is 28 years old and was born born August 3, 1992

Haag’s gaming handle, “NaDeSHoT” originates from “grenade shot”, a lethal move in the Halo series in which a grenade is followed by a gunshot Haag was a competitive amateur in the first-person shooter Halo 2, but switched to the third-person tactical shooter series, Gears of War after getting the game as a Christmas present.He narrowly missed qualifying for MLG Chicago in Gears of War play by one slot in 2007. At the age of 16 he made his professional debut on Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare.

Optic career

Haag has been a member of Optic Gaming since June 2010, when he first joined the OpTic Clan competitive team. In 2014, he became the captain of OpTic Gaming after Will “BigTymer” Johnson resigned. Haag stepped down as OpTic Gaming’s captain after a seventh-place finish at the 2015 Call of Duty Championship tournament. Nadeshot then decided to leave Optic clan in 2016.

Call of Duty: Black Ops 2010–11 season

Haag was dropped from the team for the Call of Duty: Black Ops 2011 season which was the first season of Call of Duty on the Major League Gaming circuit since Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare. He briefly returned to the Optic Competitive team, replacing a player who felt ill, at MLG Dallas where Optic Gaming finished 3rd with virtually no practice as a squad. Subsequently, after mentioning the possibility of replacing the teammate that had fallen sick he did not get picked up. Haag played on several different teams in the professional scene and created his own OpTic Nation competitive team and started making videos and streaming footage. For the next two events he played for Team EnVyUs finishing 8th at MLG Anaheim and then 3rd at MLG Raleigh before playing on Surreal Legacy for the final two events of the year placing 7th at MLG Orlando and then finishing 15th at the MLG Providence national championships to finish off the Call of Duty: Black Ops Major League Gaming season. But later got beat by a team by the name of Inspire Gaming

Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 3 2011–12 season

With Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 3 looming, Call of Duty announced Call of Duty XP where Activision hosted a $1 million tournament to showcase the newest edition of the franchise. With 2 members of the OpTic Gaming team not being available it to the Grand Final. They took t doni3-1 and Haag pocketed $100,000 with his team winning $400,000 and the trophy.

Call of Duty: Black Ops II 2012–13 season

Treyarch were to make Call of Duty: Black Ops II which was the second game in the Black Ops franchise. The game was a success competitively and attracted a bigger audience through the season. With Frag Cup 4, an annual online tournament at the start of a new Call of Duty title, coming up a member of the OpTic Gaming competitive team was unable to play due to gambling restrictions in his province, and after impressing early on in the game, OpTic Gaming picked up Haag, who rejoined the OpTic Gaming competitive team on a permanent basis. They finished in the 7th/8th position in Frag Cup 4 before going to the first LAN event which was UMG Chicago. OpTic Gaming started the tournament strong, making their way to the finals without losing. The team then lost the first series in the final. However, because they were the winners of the ‘winners final’ the match went into a final and decisive series, in which they were able to win 3-2 and become the first Call of Duty: Black Ops II champions. The next tournament was MLG Dallas. Here, the top 8 teams qualified to compete at that year’s Call of Duty Championships, which was an annual $1,000,000 event. Haag and OpTic Gaming went on to finish in the 5th/6th position. At the Call of Duty Championships, OpTic Gaming finished in third place losing to the eventual winners of the tournament. They then played in Gfinity 1 (G1) in London, United Kingdom and MLG Anaheim in Anaheim, California where were placed in third respectively at both events. The next event Haag attended was Gfinity (G2) in London. However, their new roster finished 9th–12th Their performance at the MLG Fullsail Invitational, where the four highest ranked Black Ops II teams competed, (and which was to be OpTic Gaming and MLG’s final event of the Call of Duty: Black Ops II competitive season) was much improved, finishing in second place. In first was a team by the name of Complexity Gaming

Call of Duty: Ghosts 2013–14 season

The next title of the Call of Duty franchise was Call of Duty: Ghosts which MLG announced that it would be their featured FPS title for the upcoming season again. Haag and OpTic Gaming disappointed at both of their first two events which were to be MLG Columbus (13–16th place) and UMG Philadelphia (9–12th place) before a roster change occurred with one player retiring, two leaving and one later rejoining. During this time Haag teamed with Christopher Duarte, who goes by the name of ‘Parasite’. At this time, the team consisted of ‘NaDeSHoT’, ‘Clayster’, ‘Ricky’ and ‘Parasite’. However, after only a handful of days, ‘Parasite’ and ‘Ricky’ left OpTic to join Curse Las Vegas. OpTic then picked up ‘Saints’ and ‘MBoZe’, before ‘Scumpii’ rejoined OpTic to replace the departing ‘Saints’, who returned to Strictly Business. After the retirement of ‘BigTymer’ following UMG Philadelphia, Haag became the captain of OpTic Gaming

Optic, led by Haag, qualified for the Call of Duty: Ghosts national qualifiers for the annual Call of Duty Championship $1,000,000 tournaments after qualifying via MLG’s online qualifying tournament. At the US Championship Finals OpTic Gaming finished in 7th place to qualify for the Call of Duty World Championship, after eliminating Curse New York in an elimination game in a best of 5 series. This allowed the team to qualify for the annual $1 million tournament. Haag and his OpTic Gaming squad played in the MLG Pro Circuit Season 1 online league where after a promising start they suffered problems online and were not able to qualify for the MLG PAX East Championship; eventually OpTic Gaming finished bottom of the league in 10th place. OpTic Gaming later announced that Haag and his teammates would be hosting the winners of the US Regional finals, Strictly Business Gaming for a pre-LAN event for the World Championships.

At the Call of Duty World Championships, OpTic were placed in a group with ‘Epsilon eSports’, ‘NSP’ and ‘SSOF’; controversy was caused when ‘SSOF’ were disqualified and OpTic only had two teams in their group. OpTic first played ‘NSP’ and beat them 3-0 leading to a group decider against Epsilon where Haag and his team lost 3-0. However they advanced as the second seed and faced tK in the first round of the winners bracket. Haag led his team to a 3–0 victory against a team considered to be a top three team by many. In the second round Haag was to come up against Strictly Business Gaming who they had hosted in a pre-LAN event, however Haag and his teammates won 3–2 and played Australian team Trident T1 Dotters for a guaranteed top three finish. OpTic Gaming led by Haag won the series 3–1 and guaranteed themselves 3rd and $120,000. OpTic were then to face CompLexity who were undefeated on Call of Duty: Ghosts and came up short in the winners bracket finals losing 3–2. OpTic then lost to Team EnVyUs in the losers bracket finals and Haag led his team to a top three finish and won his cut of $30,000.

Shortly after the Call of Duty World Championships, Haag signed an exclusivity contract with MLG to stream himself playing Call of Duty on MLG’s MLG.tv web streaming service. On April 15, 2014, OpTic Gaming announced that Marcus ‘MBoZe’ Blanks would be leaving the team in order for Jordan ‘ProoFy’ Cannon to join the team. The OpTic Gaming roster (Haag’s teammates) for UGC Niagara and for the 2014 season Call of Duty:Ghosts season was Seth ‘Scumpii’ Abner, James ‘Clayster’ Eubanks and Jordan ‘ProoFy’ Cannon.

At the new roster’s first tournament together, a disappointing first day lead to them having to play the world’s best team, and eventual winners of UGC Niagara, CompLexity Gaming, who proved too strong for Haag’s team. They narrowly won every map to take a 3–0 series win and knock Haag and his OpTic Gaming team out of the tournament. Before and after UGC Niagara Haag competed with his team in the MLG Pro Circuit Season 2 in order to qualify for MLG Anaheim’s pro team tournament to contest for a $70,000 prize pool. Haag’s team qualified, being second place in the league.

Haag and his OpTic Gaming team were invited to the MLG X Games on the Xbox One after finishing in the top 3 at the Call of Duty World Championships. They went into the event as underdogs after a disappointing tournament at UGC Niagara, however Haag and his team were able to win their group after beating Team EnVyUs and FaZe Red 3–1 to set up a semi final match against Evil Geniuses,(formerly known as CompLexity). Evil Geniuses were favorites to win the event after a dominant year at LAN events, but Haag and his three teammates were able to beat them 3–1 to face Team Kaliber in the Grand Finals. They managed to beat Team Kaliber in a match that came down to a Game 5, Round 10 in Search & Destroy, and Haag was able to win a Gold Medal and his first MLG Championship at the X Games in Austin, Texas.

Haag was voted by fans as The Game Awards 2014 eSports Player of the Year. He took a trip out to Las Vegas with some of his teammates and sponsors to accept this award.

Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare 2014–15 season

Advanced Warfare will be the next installment in the Call Of Duty Franchise for the e-sports circuit. The season formally began November 2014. Haag was invited by Activision to Los Angeles for a preview of Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare in order to advise developers on the state of the game. On October 28, 2014 OpTic Gaming, led by Haag, participated in an exclusive Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare streaming event at the so-called ‘OpTic House’ in Chicago, in order to promote the new edition in the franchise for its creators, Sledgehammer Games

In season opening competition, MLG Columbus, Haag and his team achieved second place, losing out to FaZe in the Grand Final. This was a sad loss for OpTic and Haag, as they hadn’t dropped a map all day until the grand finals. OpTic looked like they were going to win it all until they ran into Faze Clan in the finals. Faze narrowly took the victory, going all the way to a second best of five series.

The second tournament Haag competed in with OpTic was at UMG Orlando. Haag and his team achieved first place this time around. They went 0–2 in the first day of competition but his team managed to bounce back and with their other two games in pool play on the second day of competition. On Championship Sunday OpTic were crowned victorious as they beat a young team known as Stunner Gaming 3–1 in the grand finals.

Twelve teams qualified, including Haag’s team, for Pro League Season 1: Prophecy, FaZe, Justus, Aware, Automatic Reload, EnVyUs, Denial, eLevate, Rise Nation, Team KaLiBeR, OpTic Nation, and OpTic Gaming. Haag’s team now consists of Ian “Crimsix” Porter, Seth “Scumpii” Abner, and Matthew “Formal” Piper. OpTic Gaming were to go 38–6 in the MLG Season 1 Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare and qualified with the number one seed for the playoffs which they completed at with a $75,000 prize pool. OpTic Gaming went into the event led by NaDeSHoT and hoped to become the first team to win a LAN tournament without dropping a map. They went on to beat Rise Nation 3–0, they then came up against a team with young players called Aware Gaming who they beat 3–1 however this meant they did not become the first team to win an event without dropping a map. They then faced Team Kaliber in the winners bracket final who they narrowly beat 3–2 before progressing to the grand finals where they beat Denial eSports 3–0 to win their second event in a row. This was Haag’s second win of an MLG event after winning previously at X Games during the Call of Duty: Ghosts season.

On April 4, 2015, NaDeSHoT announced that he was stepping down as captain and member of the OpTic Gaming pro-team. He said that he will become a full-time content creator as well as co-owner of the OpTic organization. He was replaced on the lineup by Damon “Karma” Barlow.

Nadeshot Biography

Call of Duty 4 and Modern Warfare 2

Matt “NaDeSHoT” Haag, started his competitive Call of Duty career in Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare with team Genesis.
