fields.title: chocoTaco
fields.meta_title: chocoTaco Wiki, Streaming Career, Net Worth - GamerStats.net
fields.meta_description: Jake Throop, also known as ChocoTaco, is an American Twitch streamer and a seasonal PUBG esports player with more than one million followers. ChocoTaco professionally streams for Team SoloMid.
fields.overview:
Jake Throop, also known as ChocoTaco, is an American Twitch streamer and a seasonal PUBG esports player with more than one million followers. ChocoTaco professionally streams for Team SoloMid.

He was born on September 22, 1988. Choco originally grew up in Kentucky and moved to Chicago to be with his girlfriend in the early days of his streaming career. Choco also participated in Twitch Rivals and finished 6th in Squad matches, and 17th in Duo matches.
fields.body:
Early Days of ChocoTaco as a Twitch Streamer

ChocoTaco has a long gaming history and has devoted a large portion of his time to live and to stream. His live streams focus on PUBG games. ChocoTaco's skills have won him comparisons to the legendary gamer shroud and numerous other famous gamers.

Before becoming a successful streamer, Choco quit his day job and transitioned to the streaming platform full-time. 

He started streaming PUBG and quickly gained a large following. He goes live for 10 to 11 hours each day. He has also competed in PUBG 'Twitch Rivals' championship in 2019.

Choco's personal life is unknown to everyone, even to his fans. Rumors are that he has a girlfriend, but he is not quite sure about recent times. As Choco never talked about his family or personal life on streams or otherwise during public events. 

In one of his streams, he stated that he is a laidback person who prefers to do what he likes instead of worrying about the future.

ChocoTaco Streaming Career

ChocoTaco gained popularity from his PUBG gameplays as he is not just a streamer but also a sharpshooter when it comes to killing enemies and taking the ground.

Although ChocoTaco plays with various streamers on Twitch, however, during the PUBG boom, he has mostly collaborated with shroud, just9, and lurn.

Choco just not only streams PUBG, but he plays and streams various games, from the Nintendo 64 and Sega Genesis to Apex Legends and Call of Duty but not quite frequently as PlayersUnkown Battleground.

He is a 6'2" man with brown eyes and blonde hair. His body type is described as athletic. ChocoTaco has a devoted fan base on Twitch and YouTube and has over 200,000 followers on Instagram.

Aside from Twitch, ChocoTaco also has its own YouTube channel and has become one of the biggest stars in the gaming community. While he is well-known for his video gaming expertise, he has never been accused of cheating or hacking. He is one of the few gamers who has never been accused of cheating or hacking in a game.

chocoTaco Net Worth

ChocoTaco net worth is estimated between $1.5 million and $2 million. He never really talks about his business or personal life. Still, as we know, he has a YouTube channel, Twitch channel, and a merchandise website, and his income is made up of these sources.

However, this is just a vouge analysis. The calculations were based on the information publically available about ChocoTaco's businesses.

Also see: chocoTaco streaming setup

fields.title: PGL Major Antwerp 2022
fields.overview:
The PGL Major Antwerp 2022, also known as CS:GO Major or Antwerp 2022, is the biggest competitive tournament in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive pro scene. PGL Major 2022 will be the 7th CS:GO Major Championship held in Antwerp, Belgium, at the Sportpaleis. Starting from May 9th, 2022, to May 22nd, 2022.

Twenty-four teams, the qulifiers of regional tournments are going to be play against each other for the Major's trophy and US$500,000. The overall prize pool of the championship is US$1,000,000, whereas last year in PGL Major Stockholm 2021, it was US$2,000,000.

The existing Major champoin Natus Vincere, who won their first major Global Offensive championship at Stockholm in 2021.
fields.body:
Who is PGL, and What is CS:GO, Major?

PGL is an independent eSports company and one of the biggest esports tournament organizers in Europe, running and promoting events since 2002. PGL eSports organize events for Apex Legends, Dota 2, CS:GO, Clash Royale League, and various other competitive esports game.

PGL is a Romanian organization, and it will be the third Counter-Strike: Global Offensive Major hosted by them after PGL Major: Kraków 2017 and PGL Major Stockholm 2021.

CS:GO Major is the biggest professional championship in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive, where several teams play against each other for the trophy and prize money. The first CS:GO Major was in 2013 in Jönköping, Sweden, and was hosted by DreamHack with a total prize pool of US$250,000 split among 16 teams.

For more details about the CS:GO major, you can refer to this Wikipedia article.

PGL Major Antwerp 2022 Format

fields.title: Shanks
fields.meta_description: Shanks is a Canadian professional VALORANT roster for Rise Nation and a Twitch streamer where he regularly streams VALORANT. Shanks was also the part of NRG, Dignitas, and Team Underrated.
fields.overview: Ryan Ngo popularly known as Shanks is a professional VALORANT player for Rise and a streamer who has been playing video games for a very long-time. He is best known for his work in the competitive VALORANT scene, where he has won numerous tournaments and amassed a large following.
fields.body:
Shanks VALORANT Career

The 19-years-old professional VALORANT player Shanks is Vietnamese descent and currently living in Canada. He regularly streams VALORANT on Twitch along with his professional esports scene. Shanks has played VALORANT professionally for NRG, Dignitas, Team Underrated, and currently for Rise as the only roster left in the team.

Shanks as a VALORANT Roster for NRG

Ryan “shanks” Ngo was born on November 9, 1997 and currently living in Canada. In 2020, Shanks joine NRG as a Mr. 4th. The Canadian had take over the Oper role with Jett, though he did bring out Reyna when subbing in for Immortals during a First Strike qualifier. With NRG benching Yannick “KOLER” Blanchette at the same time, however, the team had yet to announce the fifth player that will round out its roster.

Shanks has had some pro VALORANT experience in the game’s short history before joining NRG. He previously trialed with Dignitas in August 2020's Pop Flash Invitational, helping the team take out TSM twice and finish in fourth place. But Dignitas ultimately decided not to sign him. The young fragger also subbed in for Immortals’ Andrew “ShoT_UP” Orlowski during the same year's UMG Closed Qualifier, aiding them in securing a spot at the main event.

In March 2021, after four months of joining NRG. Shanks left NRG VALORANT roster and explained the reason when his fans asked on Twitter, "Mutually agreed to part ways with @NRGgg. I love everyone who is apart of this org and gave me the chance to play. I had fun but this just really was not the right fit for me. Going to be streamin 8 hours a day either watch party or ranked. Still open to play with the right squad".

Shanks as a VALORANT Roster for Rise

On March 27th 2021, RiseNation annouced that they have signed Shanks along with c4Lypso in their VALORANT roster. Since then he has played 16 tourmenents with Rise and wins two of them; NSG: Summer Championship - Open 4 and Knights Monthly Gauntlet - May in May, 2021.

Shanks was also the part of team when Rise came as a runner up in VCT 2021: North America Last Chance Qualifier and lost to Cloud9 by 0:3 score. Since then he has played only played in three tournamenets. 

In March 2021, the North American organization RiseNation was also seems to selling their entire VALORANT roster to an unknown buyer. A separate group of investors then attempted to follow up on the purchase of Rise’s VALORANT team but failed to meet the deadline set by Rise.

Rise players were informed that they would be on new salaries and were “lied to” by the buyers, according to sources close to the players. At the same time in March, Rise VALORANT players Jason “Neptune” Tran and Ryan “Shanks” Ngo were set to enter restricted free agency.

The move follows the failed negotiations between the mystery buyer and Rise. Shanks along with his teammate Neptune were highly anticpating sought after in the market, but each player has not been linked with new teams, unlike their former teammates.

Later in April, 2022, FaZe Clan came with an surprising annoucement of their new VALORANT roster that was going to make its competitive debut in the VCT North American Stage Two Challengers event.

The new roster includes former Rise players Phat “suapamen” Le and Kevin “POISED” Ngo alongside Jake “Poach” Brumleve, Quan “dicey” Tran, and Andrej “Babybaby” Francisty.

However, Ryan “shanks” Ngo, who wasn’t revealed in the announcement video but rumored he would likely to join them as a content creator and he was not joined.

Currently, as of May 2022, Shanks stills is in the contract with RiseNation as the only player left in the team. As a result Shanks has not played any professional VALORANT tournament since the team fell apart and bought by FaZe Clan.

Shanks at the time focusing on his streaming career and plays VALORANT regulary.

Shanks Trivia

  • Shanks is the younger brother of poised, who is also an professional VALORANT roster and plays for FaZe Clan.

fields.title: yuurih
fields.meta_title: yuurih CS:GO Settings, Crosshair, Config & Setup
fields.overview:
Yuri Gomes dos Santos Boian is known for his aggressive and smart playstyle. He has helped lead FURIA Esports to victory in several tournaments, including the ESL Pro League Season 10 Finals and the BLAST Premier: Spring 2020 Regular Season.

With his years of experience and success, Yuri Gomes dos Santos Boian is considered to be one of the best CS: GO players in the world.

Career

Yuri Gomes dos Santos Boian is a Brazilian Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player. He is currently a member of FURIA Esports.

Yuri began his Counter-Strike career in 2012, playing Counter-Strike 1.6. He then transitioned to Counter-Strike: Source before finally moving to Counter-Strike: Global Offensive in 2014.

Yuri has been a part of some of the most successful Brazilian teams in Counter-Strike history. He was a member of the Luminosity Gaming team that won the Major at MLG Columbus 2016. He was also a member of the SK Gaming team that won the Major at ESL One Cologne 2016.

Yuri is considered to be one of the best Brazilian Counter-Strike: Global Offensive players. He is known for his aim and his ability to frag consistently.

Yuri’s career has been very successful. He has won multiple tournaments and has earned a lot of money from playing the game. He is currently one of the highest earning Counter-Strike: Global Offensive players in the world.

Achievements 

Yuri Gomes dos Santos Boian is a Brazilian professional Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player. He is currently a rifler for the Brazilian team FURIA Esports.

Achievements:

-1st place at ESWC 2015
-1st place at IEM X Gamescom 2015
-1st place at FACEIT League 2015 Stage 3
-2nd place at ESL ESEA Pro League Season 1
-Was ranked the 2nd best player of 2018 in Brazil by DRAFT5.
-Was ranked the 14th best player of 2020 by HLTV.

fields.title: KSCERATO
fields.meta_title: KSCERATO CS:GO Settings, Crosshair, Config & Setup
fields.meta_description: Kaike "KSCERATO" Silva Cerato is a Brazilian professional Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player. He is currently the Rifler for FURIA Esports.
fields.overview:
Career 

KSCERATO began his Counter-Strike career in 1.6, playing for a number of Brazilian teams including paiN Gaming and Keyd Stars. He made the switch to CS:GO in early 2014, and soon afterwards joined the lineup of Wild Gaming.

Wild Gaming saw some success in online tournaments, but it was KSCERATO's performances at offline events that began to turn heads. He helped his team to a top-eight finish at the first offline event he attended - ESL One Cologne 2014 - and followed that up with a top-four finish at the next event he attended, ESWC 2014.

 These results attracted the attention of Luminosity Gaming, who signed Wild Gaming's lineup in September 2014.

Luminosity Gaming quickly became one of the best teams in the world, thanks in large part to KSCERATO's AWPing skills. The team won a number of high-profile tournaments, including MLG Major Championship: Columbus 2016, ESL Pro League Season 3 Finals, and Intel Extreme Masters XI - World Championship.

In July 2016, KSCERATO and his Luminosity Gaming teammates made the switch to the newly-formed MiBR organization. The team has continued to find success, winning the ZOTAC Cup Masters 2018 and BLAST Pro Series: Sao Paulo 2019.

Achievements

-Was ranked the 7th best player of 2018 in Brazil by DRAFT5.
-Was ranked the 18th best player of 2020 by HLTV. 
-Was ranked the 15th best player of 2021 by HLTV..

Controversies

Kaike Silva Cerato, better known as KSCerato, is a Brazilian Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player. He is currently a member of FURIA Esports.

KSCerato has been accused of cheating in the past, most notably during his time with INTZ Esports. In December of 2016, KSCerato and his teammates were caught using an aimbot during a match against Keyd Stars. The team was later disqualified from the tournament and KSCerato was banned from competitive play for six months.

KSCerato has also been accused of match fixing. In March of 2016, KSCerato and his teammates on INTZ Esports were accused of fixing a match againstpaiN Gaming. The team was later cleared of any wrongdoing, but the accusations have still followed KSCerato to this day.

fields.title: Copenhagen Flames
fields.overview: The Copenhagen Flames is a professional esports team based in Denmark. The team was founded in 2016, and they compete in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive, League of Legends, and Overwatch. The Copenhagen Flames have qualified for several major tournaments, including the ELEAGUE Major 2017 and the Overwatch World Cup 2017. The team is owned by Sebastian Lund, who also owns the Danish esports organization North.
fields.body:
History

Copenhagen Flames have established themselves as one of the top teams in Denmark and Scandinavia. The Flames have won several tournaments and leagues, including the Copenhagen Games in 2018.

The Copenhagen Flames are known for their passionate and dedicated fan base, who support the team through thick and thin. The Flames are always looking to improve and grow their roster, and they are always striving to be the best.

The Danish team is competeting in the PGL Major Antwerp 2022 (the biggest tournament of Counter-Strike: Global Offensive). They have qualified for the quater-finals and will be competeting against ENCE to qualify for the semi-finals of CS:GO Major tournament on May 20, 2022.

vorborg (Coach) Daniel Vorborg (Coach)

Fortnite		 Swag Carl Emil Nielsen  
FlowiS Matias Albrechtsen  
FlowiS Albert Nyeborg  

Copenhagen Flames

The Danish professional esports organization, Copenhagen Flames is also involved in controversies due to the way they operate their teams. They have been accused of not paying their players on time, and of not providing adequate support for their teams. Additionally, some of the players on the Copenhagen Flames roster have been accused of cheating in online matches.

However, later the esports organization issues a series of statements regarding the cheating accustion. On Twitter they posted, "The admins of L33TCup has looked into the demos of our match against Axis The admins didn't find evidence to support unfair play, and as such the result stands, knocking us into the "Last Chance" stage. We will look at the evidence at hand ourselves, and make a statement later."

Later, the Head of Esports, Daniel Vorborg of Copenhagen Flames also issued a statement on their website.

A couple of days ago, after our 0-2 loss to Axis in L33TCup; we announced that we asked the admin team to look into suspicious behavior from the enemy team. Within the hour, the admin team said they did not have any conclusive evidence and let Axis play in the upper bracket final. We were not satisfied with the situation and decided to look into the situation ourselves.

This is us following up on the incident.

After further reconsideration, the admin team of L33TCup has decided to disqualify Axis because of evidence that one of their players was not playing fairly.

This means Navi JR and ourselves will move into the “Last Chance” Bracket.

While we are disappointed that the Axis vs Hellraisers match was not postponed to investigate the situation, which would have allowed us a chance for first place in the group, we acknowledge that the admin team has tried their best to rectify the situation.

We will continue to play from the “Last Chance” bracket, aiming to win the whole tournament.

– Daniel Vorborg, Head of Esports, Copenhagen Flames

fields.title: The new VALORANT agent’s abilities have reportedly been leaked
fields.meta_title: The new VALORANT agent’s abilities have reportedly been leaked
fields.overview: The character's release date is unknown.
fields.body:
The new agent’s abilities in VALORANT have surfaced online prior to their release, according to data miner ValorLeaks.

The new agent, codenamed ‘Bounty Hunter’ is set to be an Initiator and hails from Turkey. “This next agent should give you a more…intimate feeling when hunting down enemies,” Riot Games said about the new Agent in the State of the Agents blog post yesterday. 

The abilities are below:

Prowler 300 credits (C) 

  • Send out a creature that can follow trails or be controlled by moving your mouse. Upon reaching an enemy, they will be Nearsighted for three seconds. Only one Creature per Trail.

Seize 200 credits (Q)

  • Equip and Fire an Orb which will stay in the air for a max of 1.5 seconds, and then slam to the ground. When the orb hits the ground Enemies within the radius will be tethered, and will take damage and be deafened.

Haunt (E)

  • Equip and Fire an Orb which will stay in the air and then hit the ground. Then it will go back into the air and turn into an eye. If Enemies get seen by the eye they will be revealed and a trail debuff is applied.

Nightfall (Ultimate) 

  • Send out a wave of dark mist. If the mist hits an enemy, they will be Deafened, Trailed, and Decayed.

The release date for the new agent is not known, however.

fields.title: tucks makes return to competitive CS:GO from VALORANT
fields.meta_title: tucks makes return to competitive CS:GO from VALORANT
fields.meta_description: The former CS:GO turned VALORANT player will make his comeback under Australian team ORDER.
fields.overview: The former CS:GO turned VALORANT player will make his comeback under Australian team ORDER.
fields.body: Some news for the Australian CS:GO scene, as ORDER have announced that they are signing Tyler "⁠tucks⁠" Reilly to their roster. His signing will see him take the place of outgoing player Luke "⁠ekul⁠" Blakey. tucks started his career as a CS:GO player, representing a number of Australia-based teams but making the biggest mark with Chiefs. A hindrance to his career was a VAC ban for cheating he earned in 2014, disallowing him to participate in any Valve-sponsored events, including Majors and Major Qualifiers. The ban was lifted shortly after tucks announced his move to VALORANT in 2021, having been cleared by Valve's change to their eligability rules. Upon the release of VALORANT, he found success in the Australian scene, posting good results in tournaments under ORDER's roster in the Riot Games FPS. He has also served as a coach for the organization's CS:GO team, prior to his full-time commitment to VALORANT. tucks himself has also expressed his happiness and excitement ahead of his return. "After a decent 1.5 year stint in VALORANT, I wasn't really feeling the love for the game that I felt I should have been feeling and really wanted to make a change because it was the only thing in my life that I wasn't 100% enjoying." "After taking a little bit of time to think, I knew I still wanted to be a part of CS and within the ORDER organization. I'm so excited to be back and to be working with the ORDER CS team, I love all the guys in the roster and have a lot of respect for the talent they have and the people that they are. It's going to be a lot of fun." Most recently, he played a match for ORDER during the team's match in the ESL ANZ Championships against Renegades where they suffered a narrow 1-2 defeat. tucks' addition brings additional experience to the Australian organization's CS:GO roster who have recently reached the lower bracket finals of the Asian RMR Qualifiers and are now showing good performances in the ANZ Championships.

fields.title: s1mple featured in 30 Under 30 List for Europe 2022 by Forbes
fields.meta_title: s1mple featured in 30 Under 30 List for Europe 2022 by Forbes
fields.meta_description: s1mple, arguably the best CS:GO player globally and sometimes called AWP god, is now chosen in the Forbes 30 Under 30 List for Europe 2022.
fields.overview:
• 1mple, arguably the best CS:GO player globally and sometimes called AWP god, is now chosen in the Forbes 30 Under 30 List for Europe 2022.
  • Along with s1mple, several other esports CEOs, cofounders, and professional players were also featured in the Forbes 30 Under 30.
fields.body:
How many times do we see any esports players recognized by mainstream media? None. Right?

During the world fornite world cup in 2019, Bugha amazed everyone and won $3M in prize money. Every traditional news outlet was shocked how can a 16-years-old make so much money by just playing games.

Since then, the overall esports industry has seen enormous growth. Whether we talk about CS:GO, VALORANT, DOTA 2, or small indie games. Esports viewership is a lot more than the total sports industry combined.

The legend of AWP Oleksandr "s1mple" Kostyliev is listed by Forbes in the 30 under 30 list for Eruopes Sports and Games category.

s1mple was praised for his speech during the Intel Extreme Masters tournament in February for peace and is considered to be one of the best players in "Counter-Strike: Global Offensive" history, having been named the best player in the world by HLTV in 2018 and 2021, with runner-up finishes in 2019 and 2020.

Following these victories and rankings, Sasha won the CS:GO major 2021 held in Stockholm for Natus Vincere.

Along with s1mple, Arnau Vidal, a 23 years-old co-founder and CEO of Team Heretics, Michaela Lintrup from G2 Esports, Fabien Devide, the co-founder of Team Vitality, and some other internet personalities were also featured in the Forbes list.
fields.ref:
Source:

  • s1mple profile in Forbes list
  • Forbes 30 Under 30 List For Sports and Games Category - Europe 2022

fields.overview:

fields.body:
The moment that all CS:GO fans were waiting for is just 2 days away. On May 9th, 2022, the first PGL Major Antwerp 2022's match will be played between Challengers Stage teams. 

There are three stages for those who are not aware of this format. The Challengers Stage and Legend Stage both include 16 teams. The last is the Champions Stage, where quarter-finals, semi-finals, and grand final will be played between the winning teams of challenger and legends stage.

fields.title: Reports: 00Nation's "leo_dark" Benched
fields.meta_title: 00Nation's "leo_dark" Benched After Losing PGL Major Qualifiers
fields.meta_description: Leonardo "leo_drk" Oliveira is on the bench at 00Nation. After the team's a bad start to the year and not qualifying for the PGL Major Antwerp 2022.
fields.overview:
• Leonardo "leo_drk" Oliveira from 00Nation is benched. The actual reason is not confimed by any official member of the team or organization itself.
  • After the team's a bad start to the year and not qualifying for the PGL Major Antwerp 2022
  • Unknown whether the decision was taken by the organization, the player or by mutual agreement.
  • leo_drk is one of the players on the original 00Nation team, signed in September of last year.
  • The player signed by 00Nation last year.
fields.body:
Leonardo "leo_drk" Oliveira is on the bench at 00Nation. After the team's a bad start to the year and not qualifying for the PGL Major Antwerp 2022, the player left the starting lineup and is awaiting a proposal to leave the organization he has been defending since September last year.

According to Dust2 Brasil. It is unknown whether the decision was taken by the organization, the player or by mutual agreement, but the official announcement should happen soon.

Possible Background Story of "leo_dark" Benched

According to the report, 00Nation is already on the market looking for a replacement. Names like Rodrigo "biguzera" Bittencourt, from paiN, and Lucas "Lucaozy" Neves, from Sharks, are on the radar. As the players are the highlights of their respective teams, 00Nation will not have an easy life, and negotiations will be difficult to conclude.

leo_drk is one of the players on the original 00Nation team, signed in September of last year. Alongside Vinicius "vsm" Moreira, he was one of the only survivors of the overhaul led by Marcelo "coldzera" David, who brought with him Mario "malbsMd" Samayoa, Santino "try" Rigal and coach João "righi" Righi. Behind the scenes, there is an expectation that the team will undergo another change.

At 22, leo_drk started competing in 2016 as a professional CS:GO, player. He moved to the Sharks in Portugal. The player stayed for four years with the organization and stood out, being loaned to MIBR at the end of 2020. After the teammates did not renew with the organization, the player joined Vito "kNg" Giuseppe in Plano, signed by 00Nation last year.

fields.title: EPL S16: Shark Player's Internet Problem, Match Against B4 Postponed
fields.meta_title: Sao Caetano and Los Grandes lead in EPL Conference S16 Qualifiers
fields.meta_description: Due to an internet problem involving a Shark's player, the team's match against B4 was postponed to this Friday.
fields.overview:
• The only clash of the round of 16 that did not take place this Thursday was the one between Sharks and B4
  • Due to an internet problem involving a Shark's player, the team's match against B4 was postponed to this Friday.
  • Some players of the tryouts criticized the organizer, on Twitter.
fields.body:
The South American qualifiers for the EPL Conference Season 16 began this Thursday. Of the more than 40 participating teams, nine will go on to the second and final day of the qualifiers. São Caetano, Arctic, Stars Horizon, SWS, Meta, WINDINGO, UNO MILLE and Los Grandes advanced to the quarter-finals.

The only clash of the round of 16 that did not take place this Thursday was the one between Sharks and B4, rescheduled for this Friday at 17:00 (Brasília time) due to an internet problem involving a member of the Tubarões, as reported by the organization on Twitter.

Also, this Friday, from 18:00 (Brasília time), the quarter-finals will be played. The tryouts are the last chance for teams that still dream of playing in the ESL Pro League (EPL) Season 16. The champion will qualify for the EPL Conference S16, which gives six spots to the EPL.

Forty-seven teams in the single-elimination system are playing the South American qualifier, that is, without respect. All matches up to the semifinals are in md1, while the match validating the spot will be in md3 - it is expected to start at 8 pm, according to ESEA.

Summary of EPL Conference S16 Qualifiers

São Caetano, Arctic, Stars Horizon, Meta, UNO MILLE and Los Grandes started the tryouts for the 2nd round because they didn't have opponents in the previous one. WINDINGO was the only qualifier for the quarters that played in the opening round.

São Caetano qualified for the final clashes with triumphs over Trx Unifique Tg and ex-Blackhat. The Arctic beat Dancing Ratz and Cruzeiro, while Stars Horizon beat FirstMemory and 10org.

WINDING went through Totalega, Arena Jogue Fácil and SWS. Meta was better than PKA and River Plate. UNO MILLE defeated Player and the former Black Dragons. Los Grandes beat Redragon and Boca Juniors.

Claims

Some players of the tryouts criticized the organizer, on Twitter, concerning the number of servers available for the qualifier dispute. One of them was Gustavo "SHOOWTiME" Gonçalves.

The São Caetano player wrote, "only six servers released, and we have to wait for the other games in the sequence to roll. 200 years of CS and ESEA still hasn't learned. Fuck the South Americans, huh?".

In a similar tone, UNO MILLE member Victor "remix" Monteiro asked in a critical tone: "Hasn't ESL teamed up with FACEIT? Why does it still hold championships at ESEA? pqpppppppp" (sic).

About EPL Conference

The EPL Conference is the ESL Pro League group stage tryouts, and the competition is scheduled to be played from June 15th to 20th in Jönköping, Sweden. The award is for six places in the EPL, and the list of participants will be composed of 16 teams.

In addition to being the champion of the South American qualifier, the already qualified Outsiders, Sprout, paiN, LookingForOrg, HEET, MIBR, Rare Atom, Renegades, VERTEX, Endpoint, cowana,,, For The Win, Falcons, eClub Brugge and Lausanne will be present in the competition.

The last classified will come from Mistrzostwa Polski (Poland), Türkiye Şampiyonası (Turkey) and Master League (Portugal).

fields.title: Steam released Antwerp Major's viewer pass, stickers, and more
fields.meta_title: Steam released Antwerp Major's viewer pass, stickers, and more
fields.meta_description: Steam releases 2022's PGL Major Antwerp viewer pass, player autograph stickers, and team stickers. Everything is now available for purchase.
fields.overview:
• They say skins and stickers make you a pro in CS:GO.
  • Steam announced a new collection of team stickers, player autograph stickers, and PGL Major Antwerp's viewer pass.
  • Steam introduces a glitter version of all stickers, including the PGL Major Antwerp 2022.
fields.body:
On Wednesday, Steam, the giant game distribution service, announced the range of new stickers for CS:GO fans. The new stickers include players' autographs, team stickers, and the new major's sticker featuring "PGL Antwerp'22".

The Antwerp, autographs, and team stickers are also available in a glitter finish.

A single viewer passes for Antwerp major costs around $10, and with tokens, it's $17.50 approx. Steam also highlighted that "50% of the proceeds go to the players, teams, and organizations participating in the PGL Antwerp 2022 Major."

Team stickers CS:GO major 2022:

Users can earn up to three Souvenir Tokens with a Viewer Pass, and each token can be redeemed for a souvenir from the match of their choice.

Both players' and teams' stickers are divided into three capsule categories based on the major stages: Legends, Challengers, and Contenders. Each capsule costs around $1 with a maximum of 20 at one time (only because the option is limited to 20, I guess you can buy again after buying 1 lot of 20 if you want).

Players autographs stickers CS:GO major 2022

They also have an additional Champions Autographs Capsule, which you can't buy at the time, but the website states, "Commemorate the Champions from the 2022 Major. You'll find the winning team's players' autographs in the paper, new glitter, holo, and gold finishes."

Champions Autographs Sticker

CS:GO Major Antwerp 2022's Stickers, Viewer Pass, and Sales FAQ

I activated an Antwerp 2022 Viewer Pass, and then purchased an Antwerp 2022 Viewer Pass +3. Can I activate the Viewer Pass +3 to get the included Souvenir Tokens?

No. Only one Viewer Pass can be activated on a CS:GO account. Additional Viewer Passes can be traded or sold on the Steam Community Market.

Can I activate more than one Antwerp 2022 Viewer Pass?

No. You can only activate one Antwerp 2022 Viewer Pass on your CS:GO account.

How do I upgrade my Antwerp 2022 Event Coin?

You can upgrade your event coin by activating your pass and completing Pick'Em challenges. Complete three challenges to upgrade your coin from Bronze to Silver. Complete six challenges to upgrade your coin from Silver to Gold. If you complete all nine challenges, you'll upgrade your coin to Diamond! Each time you upgrade your coin, you'll get a Souvenir Token.

How do I get Souvenir Tokens?

There are three ways to get Souvenir Tokens: Purchase the "Viewer Pass +3" to start with 3 Souvenir Tokens; Complete challenges to upgrade your coin and earn up to 3 Souvenir Tokens; or purchase Souvenir Tokens directly once you have an activated Viewer Pass.

How many Souvenir Tokens can I earn with the Antwerp 2022 Viewer Pass?

You can earn up to three Souvenir Tokens, one each time your Antwerp 2022 Event Coin is upgraded. You can redeem your Souvenir Tokens immediately on any completed match, or hold on to them and make your decision before June 20th, 2022.

How do I redeem a Souvenir Token for a Souvenir Package?

You can redeem a Souvenir Token by inspecting your Antwerp 2022 Event Coin and visiting the Match Lister. From there, you can select any completed match to redeem it for a Souvenir Package. The souvenir you receive will feature the teams that competed in that match.

How much time do I have to redeem Souvenir Tokens for Souvenir Packages?

Souvenir Tokens can be redeemed until June 20th, 2022.

How do I participate in the Pick'Em Challenge?

The Pick'Em Challenge is part of the Antwerp 2022 Viewer Pass and unlocks after your Viewer Pass has been activated.

How do I complete challenges in the Pick'Em game?

To complete challenges in the Pick'Em game and earn progress toward upgrading your coin, you'll have to make a certain number of correct picks for each stage. In the Challengers and Legends stages, you'll have to pick five out of the nine results correctly. You can complete up to three challenges for the Champions stage: set up your bracket and correctly pick at least two of the winning Quarterfinalists, at least one winning Semi-Finalist, and the winner of the Grand Final.

Can I submit picks for the Pick'Em Challenge after a stage has begun?

No. After a stage has begun picks can no longer be made for that stage. The Challenger's Stage begins May 9th, the Legends Stage begins May 14th, and the Champions Stage begins May 19th. Get your picks in early!

fields.title: Bad News Eagle lost to FaZe in Legends Stage at PGL Major 2022
fields.meta_title: Bad News Eagle lost to FaZe in Legends Stage at PGL Major 2022
fields.meta_description: The match was a quick and fast win for FaZe in PGL Major 2022 Antwerp. FaZe took the game by the storm after round two and closed it in 1 - 1 pool by beating Bad News Eagle in the first day of Legend Stage.
fields.overview: The match was a quick and fast win for FaZe in PGL Major 2022 Antwerp. FaZe took the game by the storm after round two and closed it in 1 - 1 pool by beating Bad News Eagle in the first day of Legend Stage.
fields.body:
This match was very quick for FaZe Clan. In the first two rounds, Bad News Eagle put pressure on the American CS:GO team, but slowly and steadily after those two rounds, FaZe looked like they were coming back. 

As soon as they picked up rifles and AWPs, and were equipped with full utility, they just claimed the match by storm.

The Bad News Eagles removed Nuke and Inferno from their map pool, while FaZe removed Vertigo, Mirage, and Dust2. This left Ancient as the only map remaining. So, the match was played in the Ancient.

fields.title: NAVI vs. G2 meme war on Twitter after Major's match
fields.meta_title: NAVI vs. G2 meme war on Twitter after legend stage match; who will win
fields.meta_description: Hilarious meme war between G2 Esports and Natus Vincere after their match legend stage match. Where G2 Esports lost to NAVI in the match at PGL Major 2022 in Legends Stage.
fields.overview:
• Hilarious meme war between G2 Esports and Natus Vincere after their match legend stage match. Where G2 Esports lost to NAVI in the match at PGL Major 2022 in Legends Stage.
  • G2 posted a video where the NAVI logo stuck on the JACKz's shoe.
  • G2 also posted a picture where the in-game leader was eating the NAVI's logo banana.
  • NAVI responded with a series of tweets after this.
fields.body:
After an intense match between NAVI and G2 in Legend Stage at PGL Major Antwerp 2022, the two teams took to Twitter to engage in a hilarious meme war. It started with G2's Twitter account posting a picture of Aleksi when he was eating a banana, but the banana was hidden by the NAVI logo with the caption "ATE AND LEFT NO CRUMBS #PGLMajor." However, this was not enough to capture the intention of the Ukrainian CS:GO, team.

The G2 continued by posting a short video featuring m0NESY and JACKZ. Both were normally walking, and suddenly JACKZ's shoe was stuck into something. Both players stopped and looked, and it was NAVI's logo on JACKZ's shoe.

The European CS:GO team uploaded the video and captioned it, "RIP SHOE ᵃⁿᵈ ⁿᵃᵛᶦ."

The video sparked a response from NAVI's Twitter account and a series of ongoing memes exchange between both CS:GO teams, which posted a picture of G2's players with the caption, "Don't mess with the boys."

NAVI made fun of G2 replying to the G2's video

The Ukrainian team also tweeted, "It's just bad luck. G2 is better than NAVI. m0nesy is better than s1mple. We almost got it"

And then, "Don't forget why we call @perfectocsgo the clutch master," also replying to G2 esports.

Quick update: NAVI also wins the second match of Legend stage in PGL Major 2022 against the German team BIG by 16 - 8 score.

fields.title: m0NESY's smoke at Mirage sparked the controversy
fields.meta_title: m0NESY's smoke at Mirage sparked the controversy
fields.meta_description: A controversial smoke grenade placement on the map Mirage by m0NESY at the Major's between Imperial and G2 Esports, has been approved by PGL.
fields.overview: G2's youngest AWPer m0NESY found himself in a middle of controvery at PGL Major Antwerp. During the match between Imperial VS G2 Esports today.
fields.body:
A controversial smoke grenade placement on the map Mirage by m0NESY at the Major's between Imperial and G2 Esports, has been approved by PGL.

The placement was in question is on the B site, in the corner near the sandbags. The smoke grenade can be used to cover the entire site, making it very difficult for the attacking team to take the site.

Some people are calling for the removal of the smoke grenade placement, as they feel it is unfair and gives too much of an advantage to the defending team.

Replying to the controversy, m0NESY said, "We also asked on RMR quals tournament admins if we can use this smoke. They allowed it to use."

However, PGL has approved the placement, and it will remain in the game.

You can watch the full video here: Controversial smoke by m0NESY at PGL Major

fields.overview:

  1. Spirit VS FaZe - Match Ongoing
  2. Natus Vincere wins the quarter final match against Heroic.

  4. ENCE outs the Copenhagen Flames into semi-finals.

fields.body:
• PGL Major Antwerp 2022, Champions Stage starts on May 19th, 2022, at 09:30 CST.
  • G2 Esports, Team Vitality, and Imperial Esports finished their Major journey.
  • All eight sports on the champions stage have been booked.
  • Single-Elimination bracket matches from now onwards.

On the last day of Legends Stage, FURIA Esports and Copenhagen Flames qualified for the playoffs in the Champions stage, along with Heroic. On the other side, G2 Esports, Imperial Esports, and Team Vitality ended their journey in the PGL Major Antwerp 2022.

Champions Stage Teams

All matches of Legends Stage have been played, and qualified teams have taken all champions' stage spots. There are eight spots in the champions stage, round one starting with the Playoffs/Quarterfinals and the teams are:

  1. Team Spirit
  2. Natus Vincere
  3. ENCE
  4. Ninjas in Pyjamas
  5. FaZe Clan
  6. Copenhagen Flames
  7. Heroic
  8. FURIA Esports

Champions Stage Match Schedule

Schedule for the Playoffs/Quarterfinals in the Champions stage. The whole Champions stage has a Single-Elimination bracket, which means a team has to win all matches from now onwards to win the PGL major. A single loss will eliminate the team from the major. 

All matches are going to be the best of the three. The champions stage will begin on May 19th, 2022, with the Quarterfinals match between FaZe Clan and Ninjas in Pyjamas.

May 19, 2022

  1. FaZe VS NIP: The North American esports organization, FaZe Clan, enters the semi-finals of PGL Major Antwerp 2022 by beating the Ninjas in Pyjamas by 2 - 1. Read the full aftermath of FaZe VS NIP quarter-final's match.

fields.title: PGL Major Quarterfinal: FaZe VS NIP Lineup, Stats & Prediction
fields.meta_title: PGL Major Quarterfinal: FaZe VS NIP Lineup, Stats & Prediction
fields.meta_description: The two teams have met before with FaZe coming out on top. However, this is a best-of-three, and anything can happen. Here is a look at the lineup and stats for both teams and their players, as well as a prediction for the outcome of the series.
fields.overview:
• The first day of PGL Major Antwerp 2022's Champions Stage.
  • The first match will be played between FaZe Clan and Ninjas in Pyjamas at Antwerp's esports Arena.
  • Stats are more favourable for FaZe Clan in comparison to NIP.
  • The match is the Best of 3 (LAN) and the first Quarter-final match of the PGL Major Antwerp 2022.
  • With less than 8 hours remaining, the match will start at 16:30 CST
fields.body:
It's the first day of CS:GO PGL Major Antwerp's quarterfinals, and the first match is between the North American team FaZe and the Swedish esports organization Ninjas in Pyjamas.

FaZe Clan is up against NIP. Both teams are coming into this match with a lot of momentum, and it's sure to be a close one. FaZe Clan has been on a roll lately, winning several tournaments leading up to this event. NIP is no slouch either, they've been consistently placing well in tournaments, and they're looking to take down FaZe Clan.

From today, every match comes under a single-elimination bracket. A single match loss will entirely wipe out the team's chances of winning the biggest CS:GO tournament.

Stats wise, both teams are somewhat similar. However, NIP is at #7 in World's ranking and FaZe Clan, on the other hand, is #1. FaZe has been maintaining its number one ranking for quite a while. The Ukrainian team Natus Vincere did take the number one spot, but in the BLAST Premier event, FaZe regained its number one position in the World's ranking.

FaZe Clan VS NIP Player Roster Stats 

If we look into the statistics of each player between both teams, overall, FaZe seems to be stronger than NIP's roster players.

Both players are rifles if we compare REZ from NIP and rain from FaZe. REZ has a KPR of 0.76, and rain has 0.70. REZ has a 1.29 IMPACT score, whereas rain falls behind by 0.14 with the average IMPACT rating of 1.09.

Fun fact: Both REZ and rain are the oldest players in the current roster of both teams by joining date.

The stats contains the average of all matches played by the players in the past 3 months before their PGL Major Antwerp's quarterfinal match on May 19, 2022.

Prediction for FaZe VS NIP's Quarterfinal Match in PGL Major Antwerp 2022

Stats are mostly favouring the FaZe Clan and their strong performance in the recent matches. However, NIP is also performing well but not as much as FaZe Clan as per the stats. The second map between the NIP vs Natus Vincere match in Legends Stage was close. It was not like NIP won by a significant margin, 14 - 16. Still, NAVI won the match and took the third match by storm with an enormous margin. The final score was 16 - 4 on the Ancient map.

Whereas, FaZe hasn't had such a match for a long time, even though they took the World's number one spot from NAVI by winning the ESL Pro League Season 15 and BLAST Premier World Final 2022 on April 10 2022.

The odds are in favour of FaZe Clan, but who knows?

Who will qualify for the CS:GO Major's semi-finals today? Please tune in and share your prediction with us on Twitter @thegamerstats.

fields.title: FaZe destroyed NIP & enters into semi-finals of PGL Major
fields.meta_title: FaZe destroyed NIP & enters into semi-finals of PGL Major
fields.meta_description: The North American esports organization, FaZe Clan, enters the semi-finals of PGL Major Antwerp 2022 by brutally beating the NIP.
fields.overview:
• FaZe becomes the first team to qualify for the Semi-Finals of PGL CS: GO Major 2022.
  • NIP lost the third map, Inferno, by a significant margin.
  • ropz completely took over the match.
  • NIP's hampus solely carries the team but failed to convert into the win.
fields.body:
The North American esports organization, FaZe Clan, enters the semi-finals of PGL Major Antwerp 2022 by brutally beating the NIP. From the first map FaZe has everything under control, although they choked a bit by losing 5 rounds continuously in their own chosen map, Nuke. However, they picked up the grip and won the Nuke map by only giving 5 more rounds compared to winning 16 rounds.

In the next map, in Overpass (chosen by NIP), the same NIP choked a bit in the first few rounds, but they also tightened their grip and control over the match. Though it was still not easy for the NIP to win the Overpass, NIP's hampus supported the team single-handedly in all rounds and basically in all 3 maps. But you can't win the CS: GO's biggest tournament alone. REZ is the oldest and most experienced player in the team NIP but was not able to completely show his true skills against FaZe.

The third map was in the Inferno; apart from a few minutes in the entire match, FaZe had everything in their control. They were brutely killing each of the NIP's roster players. No matter how much they or hampus can try to carry the team. 

hampus has the highest ADR in this match, even five points more than FaZe's ropz. On the other side, FaZe was owing everything, and with the aggression of ropz and karrigan, borky, rain, and Twistzz, all FaZe roster players contributed their part and did some unique clutches, especially karrigan and borky.

fields.title: Natus Vincere vs Heroic - PGL Major Quarter-Final Match Preview
fields.meta_title: Natus Vincere vs Heroic - PGL Major Quarter-Final Match Preview
fields.meta_description: The match has begin and Natus Vincere is up against Heroic in the Quarter-finals of the PGL Major Antwerp 2022. The winning team will progress to the Semi-finals where they will face ENCE. First map is Inferno picked by Heroic, Second Ancient by Natus Vincere, and Nuke was left over as decider map.
fields.overview:
• Natus Vincere VS Heroic quarter-final match of PGL Major Antwerp 2022.
  • Wining team will face ENCE in the Semi-Finals of the CS:GO Major.
  • Last match between both team was played in PGL Major Antwerp 2022 Europe RMR A, where Heroic won the match.
fields.body:
Natus Vincere and Heroic will face off in the quarter-finals of the PGL Major 2022 on Friday. Natus Vincere are the favourites going into this match, but Heroic will be looking to exact revenge and prove that they can compete with the best teams in the world.

Natus Vincere will be up against Heroic in the Quarter-finals of the PGL Major Antwerp 2022. The winning team will progress to the Semi-finals where they will face ENCE.

The quarter-final match of the PGL Major between Natus Vincere and Heroic is going to be rememberrable match. Earlier, the last match both team played together in PGL Major Antwerp 2022 Europe RMR A, Heroic took down the Ukrainian powerhouse in an intense three-map series by winning the final two maps. NAVI is probably going to looking for the revenge and also safe their spot in the Semi-Finals of CS:GO Major.

Natus Vincere's lineup for today's match consists of Boombl4, electroNic, Perfecto, s1mple, and b1t. On the other hand, Heroic's lineup includes sjuush, stavn, TeSeS, refrezh, and cadiaN.

In the last 5 matches, Natus Vincere has won all of them against; G2 Esports, NIP, BIG, forZe, and Team Vitality. Whereas Heroic has won three matches out of the last five matches they played, they won against G2 Esports, Team Liquid, Team Vitality and lost to ENCE and Team Spirit.

Maps

First map is Inferno picked by Heroic, Second Ancient by Natus Vincere, and Nuke was left over as decider map.

fields.meta_description: The final match PGL Major Antwerp quarter-finals is won by the Ukrainian team Natus Vincere against Heroic and made into semi-finals where they will ENCE to defend their title.
fields.overview:
Match over and the summary of the match:

  1. Map 3: NAVI 16 - 8 Heroic (Nuke)
  2. Map 2: NAVI 16 - 14 Heroic (Ancient)
  3. Map 1: NAVI 10 - 16 Heroic (Inferno)
  4. Man of the Match: electroNic 75/52 (K/D), 102 (ADR), 80% (KAST), and 1.46 (Rating 2.0) 

Natus Vincere VS Heroic quarter-final match of PGL Major Antwerp 2022. The Ukrainian powerhouse made into the semi-finals and beats the Heroic by 2 - 1 and their revenge of losing the match in PGL Major Antwerp 2022 Europe RMR A, where Heroic won the match.
fields.body:
Natus Vincere will face ENCE in the semi-finals of CS:GO major and to defect their title.

Denis 'electroNic' Sharipov, tops the chart of players' stats with most kills and become the man of the match.

Map 3 Nuke: Heroic win the round 16. @tesescsgo took 3 in a row with pistol. NAVI 12 - 4 Heroic
Map 3 Nuke: @natusvincere wins the last round, 15 of first half. @s1mpleO finally made his move and NAVI 4 rounds away from the semi-finals. NAVI 12 - 3 Heroic

Map 3 Nuke: NAVI wins the round 7. Heroic saves in the round. NAVI 6 - 1 Heroic Winning Streak: NAVI - 6.

Map 3 Nuke: NAVI wins three rounds straight. NAVI 3 - 1 Heroic
Map 3 Nuke: NAVI wins the round 3. NAVI 2 - 1 Heroic
Map 3 Nuke: Heroic took the pistol round from NAVI. NAVI 0 - 1 Heroic
NAVI vs Heroic Map 3 started at Nuke
electroNic becomes the best player by K/D after map 2 with 45-34, and cadiaN moves to second position with 42-31.
s1mple beats the cadiaN in the second map as a best AWPer. 
NAVI won the second map by 16 - 14 against Heroic on Ancient.
Heroic is making the NAVI sweat hard because the Ukrainian team is the king of the Ancient map.
electroNic is playing the most crucial role in the team, and snatching the final round of the first half by faking the plant was an absolute killer.
The Ukrainian powerhouse got some rounds in the second half, but Heroic is giving tough competition.
Map 2: NAVI struggles to gain the margin on their favourite map in half.
Casper 'cadiaN' Møller tops the list of best player by K/D (22-11) so far followed by Denis 'electroNic' Sharipov with 19-15.
Natus Vincere lost the first map, Inferno, by 10 - 16 to Heroic. Heroic seems to be controlling the map, whereas NAVI is struggling to make their moves.
CadiaN played amazingly great in the first map and scored the most, even higher than the s1mple.
The PGL Major Antwerp quarter-finals are underway, with NAVI taking on Heroic. The first map is Inferno, picked by Heroic, Second Ancient by Natus Vincere, and Nuke was left over as a decider map.

Map picking

  1. Heroic removed Dust2
  2. Natus Vincere removed Vertigo
  3. Heroic picked Inferno
  4. Natus Vincere picked Ancient
  5. Natus Vincere removed Overpass
  6. Heroic removed Mirage
  7. Nuke was left over

fields.title: PGL Major Antwerp: Semifinal's Match NAVI VS ENCE Lineup, Schedule
fields.meta_title: ENCE looking to repeat the history at PGL Major Antwerp
fields.meta_description: Natus Vincere vs ENCE is the second match of PGL Major Antwerp's semifinals. ENCE is looking forward to repeating history by beating Natus Vincere in the semifinals.
fields.body:
Natus Vincere vs ENCE is the second match of PGL Major Antwerp's semifinals. ENCE is looking forward to repeating history by beating Natus Vincere in the semifinals. Previously, in 2019's Counter-Strike Major, ENCE and NAVI faced each other in the semifinals, and ENCE won the best of 3 matches by 2 - 1.

At that time, allu was the match's hero and carried ENCE to the finals, but this time, Natus Vincere is not the same old one. They are the defending champions in this year's Major and the favourites. Share your thoughts on the match with us @thegamerstats on twitter.

fields.title: TenZ
fields.meta_title: TenZ's Settings, Keybinds, and Crosshair for VALORANT
fields.overview:
Tyson “TenZ” Ngo or “Sentinels TenZ” (formerly C9 TenZ) is a professional VALORANT roster for Sentinels. TenZ started playing professional VALORANT in 2020 and officially announced his retirement from the professional Counter-Strike: Global Offensive pro scene. 20-years-old TenZ also streams on Twitch and publishes his VALORANT highlights videos on YouTube.

Here we've covered TenZ's setup, including mouse, keyboard, graphics card, mousepad, keyboard, and everything you need to know about his gaming gear and peripherals.
fields.settings_body:
TenZ VALORANT Settings: The most recent and up to date information about TenZ's VALORANT Sensitivity, Video Settings, Keybinds, Setup & Config. Below we have covered the TenZ VALORANT Settings including Sensitivity, Video Settings and Keybinds.

TenZ Valorant Video Settings: 

  • Display Mode: Fullscreen
  • Fullscreen Resolution: 1920×1080
  • Aspect Ratio: 16:9
  • Refresh Rate: 240Hz
  • In-game Resolution: 1920×1080
  • Texture Quality: Low
  • Effects Quality: Low
  • Shadow Quality: Low
  • Anti-Aliasing: Off
  • V-Sync: Off Motion Blur
fields.setup_body:
TenZ did a PC build stream and later published a video on YouTube titled "BUILDING MY $5000 GAMING PC - C9 TenZ." He used a GeForce RTX 3090 graphics card, which was just released a month ago when TenZ did that PC build stream. 

He built his gaming PC with an AMD Ryzen 9 5900X CPU, Lian Li O11D XL-X ATX Full Tower case, G.Skill Trident Z (16 GB X 2), and etc.

However, if you follow TenZ or ever watched him playing VALORANT at the competitive level. You must have a fair idea of how much he loves to change his specs and settings. Tyson, aka TenZ is always known for changing his PC specs, even during competitive esports matches. 

TenZ constantly changes his gear, especially the mouse, and adjusts his sensitivity, crosshair placement, and general in-game settings. And the video is almost 1.5 years old. So, it's not fair to analyze that VALORANT roster is still using those exact old computer specifications.

So, below we have mentioned the most recent and updated PC specs and VALORANT gaming setup of Sentinal's TenZ.

fields.title: shroud
fields.overview:
shroud is a former professional CS:GO player and is widely considered to be one of the best shooters in the world. He is currently a full-time Twitch streamer and mostly plays VALORANT and Escape from the Tarkov. shroud has a ability to quickly established himself as one of the best players in the game, known for his incredible aim and game sense.

shroud's VALORANT settings are pretty standard and below we have mentioned everything in detail.
fields.settings_body:
In August 2019, Shroud announced his retirement. He cited boredom and a desire to pursue other interests as his reasons for leaving the scene. Despite his retirement, shroud still remains one of the most popular gamer in CS:GO community, then it was PUBG, and more recently in 2022 he is spending majority of his time playing and streaming VALORANT.

He once even mentioned, he might consider joining the pro screne again as a professional VALORANT player. shroud recently has also become a fan boy of TenZ as he continue to involve more and more in VALORANT and here we have covered shroud's VALORANT settings which every fan desperately want to know about his VALORANT in-game settings, sens, crosshair, and setup.

Shroud's VALORANT Settings are as follows:

  • Shroud's VALORANT Settings Resolution: 1920x1080
  • Crosshair: Green
  • Sensitivity: 0.75
  • DPI: 400
  • In-game sens: 0.75
fields.setup_body:
shroud's gaming setup is simple but effective, consisting of a custom-built PC, a BenQ XL2546 24.5-inch 240Hz monitor, i7-8700k CPU, an ASUS ROG STRIX Z370-E motherboard, an NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1080 Ti GPU, G.SKILL Trident Z RGB 32GB RAM, a Samsung 960 Pro 512GB SSD, a WD Black 4TB HDD, and an ASUS ROG Swift PG279Q monitor. He uses a HyperX Cloud II headset, a Logitech G810 Orion Spectrum RGB keyboard, and a Logitech G502 Proteus Spectrum RGB mouse.

For his streaming setup, Shroud uses an Elgato HD60 Pro capture card, an ASUS ROG STRIX Flare RGB mechanical keyboard, and a Logitech C920 webcam.

fields.settings_body:
s1mple has played for a number of teams, including HellRaisers and Team Liquid. He is currently on Natus Vincere, where he has been since 2016. s1mple is considered one of the best CS:GO players in the world.

He is known for his amazing aim and his ability to hit consistent headshots. He is also known for his aggressive playstyle and his willingness to take risks. He has won numerous tournaments and has been ranked as the #1 player in the world by HLTV.org.

s1mple's CS:GO settings are optimized for maximum performance. He uses a high sensitivity and a low resolution to give himself the best possible aim. s1mple's settings are also geared towards giving him the best possible game sense.
fields.setup_body:
s1mple gaming setup is designed to give him the edge he needs to win. It includes a high-end gaming PC, a top-of-the-line gaming monitor, a comfortable gaming chair, and a custom-built gaming desk. His CS:GO setup is designed to give him the best possible gaming experience.

s1mple computer monitor is a BenQ XL2546, which gives him a clear view of the game. He uses a HyperX Cloud II gaming headset to communicate with his team. s1mple uses a Razer BlackWidow Chroma keyboard, which he uses to type commands quickly and accurately. His mouse is a Razer DeathAdder Chroma, which gives him precise control over his game.

fields.overview:
Shivam Patel, better known as ShivFPS is a professional Apex Legends player who is currently a content creator for Luminosity Gaming. Shiv is a 24-years-old Apex professional who was born on May 11, 1998. Shiv rose to prominence early on in Apex and he remains one of the game’s most popular streamers, popular for his ability to reach high ranks consistently despite often solo-queuing.

He has 1.4 million followers on Twitch and over 300k subscribers on YouTube, where he shares the highlights of the stream.

fields.overview:
Andrej Francisty better known as babybay or FaZe babybay is an American VALORANT professional for FaZe Clan and a former professional Overwatch esports player. The VALORANT roster is of Slovak and Lebanese descent.

Andrej has also been a professional CrossFire player for Team Carbon. The fragger has over 185k followers on Twitch and regularly streams VALORANT on Twitch. Since the beginning of this year, babybay has maintained a decent kill to death ratio over his competitors and can land victories in most of the matches he played in with FaZe Clan.

fields.overview:
Ethan Arnold or famously known as just Ethan is a professional VALORANT roster player for NRG Esport's VALORANT division. Ethan is also a retired Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player and known for his professional time in NRG Esports and Evil Geniuses. The VALORANT star is 22-years-old from the United States and was born on March 2, 2000.

Before joining NRG's VALORANT roster Ethan has played for 100 Theives and in April 2022 he becomes inactive, and in a couple of days entered into a new contract with NRG Esports.
